ig) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QM1ACEQTHDWFRyRNnkYMfh","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RKjKR9SCzgFS5c4ZJuUq49","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jo7TWzWDHPSagtwvRoPxwR","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/index.md","content":"# Implementation Tasks\n\n| Group | Title | Tasks | Total Effort | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| [TG-01](TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md) | Infrastructure & Scaffold | 2 tasks | ~2 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-02](TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md) | Backend Analysis Pipeline | 7 tasks | ~12 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-03](TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md) | Backend API & Output | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-04](TG-04-frontend/index.md) | Frontend | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-05](TG-05-integration-qa/index.md) | Integration & QA | 1 task | ~2 days | PENDING |\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019astw6Lq3g7mFdAwjZvkzM","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md","content":"# TG-01: Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n## Description\n\nEstablishes the monorepo directory layout, Docker Compose development environment, Python and Node.js dependency manifests, and all project-level configuration files. This group delivers the skeleton that every other task depends on.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md) | Project Scaffold & Docker Compose | M | — | LOW |\n| [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md) | Backend Config & App Factory | S | T-001 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (full parallel): 1 day\n- Realistic (1 dev, sequential): 2 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01ALe6zdYN6qunPZe2gxhQGj","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md","content":"# T-001: Project Scaffold & Docker Compose\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** monorepo root, Docker Compose\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** —\n- **Blocks:** [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md), [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nCreate the complete monorepo directory structure for PhotoCop: the `backend/` Python project, the `frontend/` Vite/React/TypeScript project, the `docker-compose.yml` for development, and all project-level configuration files (`.env.example`, `.gitignore`, dependency manifests). No implementation logic is included — only the scaffold that gives every subsequent task a valid working directory.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Project Scaffold\n\n  Scenario: Docker Compose starts both services successfully\n    Given the repository root contains a valid docker-compose.yml\n    When a developer runs docker compose up --build\n    Then both backend (port 8000) and frontend (port 5173) containers start without errors\n    And the backend healthcheck passes within 30 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Backend stub health endpoint responds\n    Given the Docker Compose stack is running\n    When a client sends GET http://localhost:8000/health\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body is {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: TypeScript strict mode is enforced\n    Given frontend/tsconfig.json exists\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains \"strict\": true\n    And it contains \"noImplicitAny\": true\n\n  Scenario: All required environment variables are documented\n    Given .env.example exists in the repository root\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains entries for MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES, ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, CORS_ORIGINS, ELA_WEIGHT, NOISE_WEIGHT, CLONE_WEIGHT, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED, HEATMAP_ALPHA\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `pyproject.toml` must declare runtime deps: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `pydantic>=2`, `pydantic-settings`, `pillow`, `numpy`, `opencv-python-headless`, `scikit-image`, `python-magic`, `filetype`, `exifread`, `piexif`.\n- `frontend/package.json` must declare: `react@^18`, `react-dom@^18`, `typescript`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`, `msw`.\n- `backend/tests/fixtures/` directory must contain placeholder files `authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`.\n- Docker healthcheck: `curl -f http://localhost:8000/health`, interval 30s, timeout 5s, retries 3.\n- `.gitignore` must exclude `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env`, `dist/`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] `docker compose up --build` succeeds end-to-end\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`\n- [ ] `.env.example` documents all environment variables from L1/L2 design\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01NY8gznnMSph4tbdkSTTUox","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md","content":"# T-002: Backend Config & App Factory\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** FastAPI Backend — `config.py`, `main.py`, `errors.py`, `dependencies.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the Pydantic `Settings` model (`config.py`), the FastAPI application factory (`main.py`), the global exception handler producing RFC 7807 `ProblemDetails` responses (`errors.py`), and the `get_settings` dependency factory (`dependencies.py`). The `Settings` model must validate at startup that `ELA_WEIGHT + NOISE_WEIGHT + CLONE_WEIGHT == 1.0`; a misconfigured environment must cause a hard startup failure.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Backend Config & App Factory\n\n  Scenario: Settings load from environment variables with correct defaults\n    Given no environment variables are set\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then max_upload_bytes equals 10485760\n    And analysis_timeout_seconds equals 9\n    And cors_origins equals [\"http://localhost:5173\"]\n\n  Scenario: Settings validation rejects weights that do not sum to 1.0\n    Given ELA_WEIGHT=0.5, NOISE_WEIGHT=0.3, CLONE_WEIGHT=0.3 are set in the environment\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then a ValidationError is raised\n    And the error message references weight sum constraint\n\n  Scenario: Unhandled exception returns RFC 7807 ProblemDetails\n    Given the FastAPI application is running\n    When a request triggers an unhandled internal exception\n    Then the response status is 500\n    And the Content-Type header is application/problem+json\n    And the response body contains \"type\", \"title\", \"status\", \"detail\" fields\n    And the \"detail\" field does not contain a stack trace or internal file path\n\n  Scenario: CORS allows configured origin and blocks others\n    Given CORS_ORIGINS is set to http://localhost:5173\n    When a preflight OPTIONS request arrives from http://evil.example.com\n    Then the response does not include Access-Control-Allow-Origin for that origin\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings` for `Settings`; all env var aliases match the names in `.env.example`.\n- `@model_validator(mode=\"after\")` on `Settings` checks weight sum; tolerance of 1e-6 acceptable for float arithmetic.\n- `python-magic` requires OS-level `libmagic1`; Dockerfile must include `apt-get install -y libmagic1`. Missing library causes `ImportError` at startup, not at request time.\n- Global exception handler must log the internal exception at ERROR level (exception type + message) but must never include the traceback in the HTTP response.\n- `get_settings` uses `@lru_cache()` so Settings is a singleton per process.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Weight sum validator tested with both valid and invalid float combinations\n- [ ] RFC 7807 response shape verified by test against actual exception\n- [ ] No PII in logs (EXIF values must never appear)\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01H2p4ZL4cipdHxknTRm9nEG","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md","content":"# TG-02: Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete forensic image analysis pipeline: Image Ingestion Service (magic-byte validation and PIL decoding), the three forensic analysers (ELA, Noise, Clone Detection), the Score Aggregator, and the Analysis Engine orchestrator that fans out to the analysers concurrently. This group delivers the core intelligence of PhotoCop.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md) | Image Ingestion Service | M | T-002 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md) | ELA Analyser | M | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md) | Noise Analyser | M | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md) | Clone Detector | L | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md) | Score Aggregator | S | T-004, T-005, T-006 | LOW |\n| [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md) | Analysis Engine Orchestrator | M | T-007 | HIGH |\n| [T-009](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-009-heatmap-renderer.md) | (see TG-03) | — | — | — |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (full parallel on T-004/T-005/T-006): 5 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 8–10 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019K8LQbUiA5dPTPxSPq6Ucv","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md","content":"# T-003: Image Ingestion Service\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Image Ingestion Service — `backend/app/ingestion.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-002](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md), [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `ImageBuffer` dataclass and the `ingest` function in `backend/app/ingestion.py`. The function reads raw bytes from the FastAPI `UploadFile`, validates the file size, performs magic-byte detection using `python-magic` (with `filetype` as pure-Python fallback), decodes the validated bytes into a normalised PIL `Image`, and returns an `ImageBuffer`. All error paths raise a typed `IngestionError` with a `code` field that the API router maps to the correct HTTP status.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Image Ingestion Service\n\n  Scenario: Valid JPEG is accepted and decoded\n    Given raw bytes of a 3 MB valid JPEG file\n    When ingest() is called with those bytes and content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an ImageBuffer is returned\n    And ImageBuffer.format equals \"JPEG\"\n    And ImageBuffer.image is a PIL Image in RGB or RGBA mode\n    And ImageBuffer.raw_bytes equals the original input bytes\n\n  Scenario: File exceeding size limit raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a file with size greater than MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"SIZE_EXCEEDED\"\n\n  Scenario: File with mismatched magic bytes raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a PDF file renamed with .jpg extension\n    When ingest() is called with content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\"\n\n  Scenario: Unsupported format (GIF) raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a valid GIF image\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\"\n\n  Scenario: Truncated image bytes raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes with valid JPEG magic bytes but truncated binary content\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"DECODE_FAILED\"\n\n  Scenario: No data is written to disk at any point\n    Given valid image bytes are provided to ingest()\n    When ingest() completes (success or failure)\n    Then no files are created in the filesystem\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `python-magic` for magic-byte detection; fall back to `filetype` if `python-magic` import fails (i.e., libmagic not installed). Never use `imghdr` (removed in Python 3.13).\n- Supported formats and their magic signatures: JPEG (`FF D8 FF`), PNG (`89 50 4E 47`), WebP (`52 49 46 46...57 45 42 50`), TIFF (`49 49 2A 00` or `4D 4D 00 2A`), BMP (`42 4D`).\n- `ImageBuffer` is a `@dataclass` with fields: `image: PIL.Image.Image`, `raw_bytes: bytes`, `format: str`, `size_bytes: int`.\n- `IngestionError` carries a `code: Literal[\"SIZE_EXCEEDED\", \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\", \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\", \"DECODE_FAILED\"]` field.\n- PIL decoding: open from `io.BytesIO(raw_bytes)`, call `image.convert(\"RGB\")` for non-alpha formats.\n- Security: never write to disk; never execute uploaded bytes.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Tests use fixture files: `corrupt.bin`, `authentic.jpg`, `no_exif.jpg`, plus a synthetic oversized blob\n- [ ] No PII in logs (raw bytes must never be logged)\n- [ ] `python-magic` fallback to `filetype` tested via monkeypatched import\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01U6mdxkhdT3Kng8YCYwC4va","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-004-ela-analyser.md","content":"# T-004: ELA Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the ELA (Error Level Analysis) forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`. The analyser re-saves the image at a known JPEG quality level, computes the absolute pixel difference between original and re-saved versions, amplifies the result, and identifies high-anomaly zones as `RegionResult` objects. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"ELA\"`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: ELA Analyser\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg (read-only copy)\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"ELA\"\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns elevated sub-score for a known-manipulated image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/manipulated.png (read-only copy)\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions is a non-empty list\n\n  Scenario: ELA does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: ELA handles a heavily-compressed JPEG without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image of a highly compressed JPEG (quality < 30)\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n    And sub_score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n\n  Scenario: ELA with invalid quality parameter raises ValueError\n    Given a PIL Image\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=0) is called\n    Then a ValueError is raised\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Re-save to `io.BytesIO` at specified quality using `PIL.Image.save(buf, format=\"JPEG\", quality=quality)`.\n- Amplify difference: `diff = ImageChops.difference(original, resaved)`; scale to `[0, 255]` range for visualisation.\n- Identify high-anomaly zones: threshold at mean + 2*std of the difference map; connected-component labelling via `skimage.measure.label`.\n- Each connected component above minimum area becomes a `RegionResult` with `technique=\"ELA\"`.\n- `confidence` per region = normalised mean ELA value in that region.\n- Sub-score = proportion of pixels above threshold, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Never write intermediate buffers to disk.\n- Quality parameter range: 1–95 (validate; raise `ValueError` outside range).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Immutability of input image verified by pixel comparison test\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] — asserted in all test paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DS7qErdpw821kPkKVhAjyb","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-005-noise-analyser.md","content":"# T-005: Noise Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the noise-inconsistency forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`. The analyser computes a noise residual map by subtracting a Gaussian-filtered version of the image from the original, then identifies regions with statistically anomalous noise variance. Inconsistent noise patterns indicate splicing or copy-paste manipulation. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"noise_analysis\"`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Noise Analyser\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg (read-only copy)\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"noise_analysis\"\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser detects inconsistency in a spliced image\n    Given a PIL Image constructed by pasting a region from a different image\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions contains at least one entry whose bounding_box overlaps the pasted region\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser handles a grayscale image without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image in mode \"L\" (grayscale)\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Convert image to grayscale numpy array before filtering.\n- Apply `scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter` (sigma configurable, default 2) to produce denoised version.\n- Residual = `original_gray - denoised_gray` (absolute values).\n- Compute local variance using sliding window (e.g. `skimage.filters.rank.variance` or manual convolution).\n- Regions with local variance > mean + 2*std are flagged.\n- Connected-component labelling via `skimage.measure.label`; each component above minimum area becomes a `RegionResult`.\n- Sub-score = proportion of pixels above variance threshold, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Input image must not be mutated; work on a copy.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_014e7fMFp9XcNJEvDVNdUJiH","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-006-clone-detector.md","content":"# T-006: Clone Detector\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** L\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement copy-move forgery detection in `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`. The detector computes ORB keypoint descriptors, clusters matched descriptor pairs, and identifies spatially distinct image patches that share high-confidence descriptor matches — evidence of copy-move forgery. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"clone_detection\"`. Images must be downsampled to at most 1024 px on the longest edge before descriptor computation to stay within the performance budget.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Clone Detector\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg (read-only copy)\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.3\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"clone_detection\"\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector identifies copy-moved regions\n    Given a PIL Image with a known duplicated region (one quadrant copied from another)\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions contains at least two entries\n    And the bounding boxes of those entries are spatially non-adjacent\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector completes within time budget for a 10 MB image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from a 10 MB JPEG fixture\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the function returns within 3 seconds\n    And an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns empty regions when no matches exceed threshold\n    Given a PIL Image with no duplicate regions\n    When clone_detect(image, min_match_threshold=10) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.regions is an empty list\n    And AnalyserOutput.sub_score is 0.0\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Downsample image to max 1024 px longest edge before ORB computation using `PIL.Image.thumbnail` (aspect-ratio preserving).\n- Use `cv2.ORB_create(nfeatures=1000)` for descriptor extraction.\n- Match descriptors with `cv2.BFMatcher(cv2.NORM_HAMMING)` and apply ratio test (Lowe's ratio 0.75).\n- Cluster matched pairs; spatially distinct pairs (centroid distance > 10% of image dimension) are copy-move candidates.\n- Scale bounding boxes back to original image coordinates after detection at downsampled resolution.\n- Sub-score = number of confirmed clone pairs / (number of clone pairs + 10), clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- `min_match_threshold` parameter (default 5): minimum number of matching descriptors to declare a clone.\n- Never mutate input image; always work on a downsampled copy.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Performance test with 10 MB fixture confirms < 3 s completion\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XxWKTud4ByU2Ufi2p2YKZx","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-007-score-aggregator.md","content":"# T-007: Score Aggregator\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py` containing the `ScoreAggregator` that accepts three `AnalyserOutput` objects, computes a weighted average score, derives the verdict string from configurable thresholds, and merges all region lists into a deduplicated `PipelineResult`. Weights and thresholds are read from `Settings`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Score Aggregator\n\n  Scenario: Weighted average score is computed correctly\n    Given ELA sub-score 0.8, noise sub-score 0.2, clone sub-score 0.0\n    And weights ELA=0.4, noise=0.3, clone=0.3\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then the returned PipelineResult.score equals 0.38 (within 1e-6 tolerance)\n\n  Scenario: Score in range [0.0, 0.3] produces \"authentic\" verdict\n    Given aggregate() returns a weighted score of 0.2\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"authentic\"\n\n  Scenario: Score in range (0.3, 0.7) produces \"suspicious\" verdict\n    Given aggregate() returns a weighted score of 0.5\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"suspicious\"\n\n  Scenario: Score in range [0.7, 1.0] produces \"likely manipulated\" verdict\n    Given aggregate() returns a weighted score of 0.85\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"likely manipulated\"\n\n  Scenario: All regions from all analysers appear in the merged output\n    Given ELA returns 2 regions and clone returns 1 region and noise returns 0 regions\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.regions contains exactly 3 entries\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `PipelineResult` is a `@dataclass` with `score: float`, `verdict: str`, `regions: list[RegionResult]`.\n- Score = `ela_weight * ela_score + noise_weight * noise_score + clone_weight * clone_score`.\n- Verdict thresholds read from `Settings.verdict_threshold_authentic` (default 0.3) and `Settings.verdict_threshold_manipulated` (default 0.7).\n- Region list is the concatenation of all three region lists; no deduplication logic required at this stage (regions from different techniques have different `technique` fields).\n- Score is clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]` after computation as a defensive guard.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Score boundary conditions tested at exactly 0.3 and 0.7\n- [ ] Region count verified in all three-analyser combinations\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01YGWEPvZavg31MApaGsySgp","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md","content":"# T-008: Analysis Engine Orchestrator\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/engine.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-009](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-009-heatmap-renderer.md), [T-010](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-010-exif-extractor.md), [T-011](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-011-response-assembler.md), [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/analysis/engine.py` — the `run_pipeline` async function that receives an `ImageBuffer`, fans out to all three analysers concurrently using `asyncio.gather` over a `ThreadPoolExecutor`, collects `AnalyserOutput` objects, passes them to the `ScoreAggregator`, and returns a `PipelineResult`. Each analyser receives an independent `Image.copy()` to guarantee read-only isolation. The outer function enforces the `ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` hard limit via `asyncio.wait_for`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Analysis Engine Orchestrator\n\n  Scenario: All three analysers are called and results are aggregated\n    Given an ImageBuffer containing a valid PIL Image\n    And mock implementations of ela_analyse, noise_analyse, and clone_detect are injected\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then all three mock analysers were called exactly once\n    And run_pipeline returns a PipelineResult with score and verdict populated\n\n  Scenario: Each analyser receives a distinct copy of the image\n    Given an ImageBuffer containing a PIL Image\n    And spy wrappers around each analyser recording the image object identity\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then each analyser received a different Python object (id(image) differs per analyser)\n    And the original ImageBuffer.image was not passed directly to any analyser\n\n  Scenario: Analysis timeout raises asyncio.TimeoutError\n    Given an ImageBuffer and ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS set to 1\n    And a mock ELA analyser that sleeps for 5 seconds\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then asyncio.TimeoutError is raised within 2 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Pipeline result is a PipelineResult with valid score range\n    Given an ImageBuffer from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then a PipelineResult is returned\n    And PipelineResult.score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n    And PipelineResult.verdict is one of \"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `run_pipeline` is `async def`; analysers run in `loop.run_in_executor(executor, analyser_fn, image_copy)`.\n- Use `ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=3)` created at module level (not per-request, to avoid thread churn).\n- `asyncio.gather` with `return_exceptions=False` so any analyser exception propagates immediately.\n- `asyncio.wait_for(gather_coro, timeout=settings.analysis_timeout_seconds)` enforces the hard limit.\n- Image copies: `ela_img = image_buffer.image.copy()`, `noise_img = image_buffer.image.copy()`, `clone_img = image_buffer.image.copy()` before dispatch.\n- On `asyncio.TimeoutError`: let it propagate to the router, which maps it to HTTP 504.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Image copy isolation verified by object identity test\n- [ ] Timeout behaviour tested with a slow mock analyser\n- [ ] No shared mutable state between concurrent calls verified by parallel-request test\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_017pFsa7F8rrAzziRKr8gpTQ","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md","content":"# TG-03: Backend API & Output\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend API & Output\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the four output-facing backend components: Heatmap Renderer (coloured overlay as base64 data URI), EXIF Extractor (privacy-safe metadata parsing), Response Assembler (Pydantic `AnalysisResponse` model), and the FastAPI Router with middleware, error handlers, and CORS configuration. This group delivers the complete, runnable backend API.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-009](T-009-heatmap-renderer.md) | Heatmap Renderer | M | T-008 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-010](T-010-exif-extractor.md) | EXIF Extractor | S | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md) | Response Assembler | S | T-008, T-009, T-010 | LOW |\n| [T-012](T-012-fastapi-router.md) | FastAPI Router & Middleware | M | T-011 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-009 and T-010 in parallel): 3 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 4–5 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QGEFbhqRvhNmpbeDc8iCR4","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-009-heatmap-renderer.md","content":"# T-009: Heatmap Renderer\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** Heatmap Renderer — `backend/app/heatmap.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-008](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/heatmap.py` — the `render` function that composites a colour-coded overlay of `RegionResult` bounding boxes onto the original PIL image and returns the result as a `data:image/png;base64,...` data URI string. High-confidence regions are rendered red, low-confidence regions yellow-green. On empty regions list, returns the original image as a data URI unchanged. If compositing fails for any region, logs a WARNING and continues without that region.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Heatmap Renderer\n\n  Scenario: Non-empty regions produce a data URI with overlay\n    Given a PIL Image and a list with one RegionResult at confidence 0.9\n    When render(image, regions, alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then the returned string starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And the base64-decoded bytes represent a valid PNG image\n\n  Scenario: Empty regions list returns the original image as data URI\n    Given a PIL Image and an empty regions list\n    When render(image, regions=[], alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then the returned string starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And the decoded PNG has the same dimensions as the original image\n\n  Scenario: Renderer does not write any files to disk\n    Given a PIL Image and any regions list\n    When render() is called\n    Then no files are created in the filesystem\n\n  Scenario: Malformed bounding box is skipped with a WARNING log, not an exception\n    Given a PIL Image and a RegionResult with bounding_box x=-1, y=-1, width=-1, height=-1\n    When render(image, regions, alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then a valid data URI is returned (original image unchanged)\n    And a WARNING-level log entry was emitted\n    And the WARNING message does not contain image pixel data\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `PIL.Image`, `PIL.ImageDraw` for overlay compositing.\n- Colour map: `confidence` 0.0 → yellow-green (R=180, G=255, B=0), `confidence` 1.0 → red (R=255, G=0, B=0). Linear interpolation.\n- Alpha parameter (default 0.5, read from `Settings.heatmap_alpha`): controls overlay opacity.\n- Composite using `PIL.Image.blend` or `paste` with an RGBA mask.\n- Encode to PNG via `io.BytesIO`; encode result with `base64.b64encode`; prepend `\"data:image/png;base64,\"`.\n- Never write to disk; release all intermediate PIL objects after data URI is produced.\n- On `IndexError` or `ValueError` from malformed bounding box: log `WARNING \"Heatmap: skipping malformed region\"` (no pixel data in message) and continue.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] No PII in logs (no pixel data, no EXIF values)\n- [ ] Output is always a valid base64-encoded PNG (verified by decoding in test)\n- [ ] No disk writes verified by mocking filesystem in test\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_018w6HMoe8ujq5Ga97CbJdmp","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-010-exif-extractor.md","content":"# T-010: EXIF Extractor\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** EXIF Extractor — `backend/app/exif.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/exif.py` — the `extract` function that accepts raw image bytes, attempts EXIF parsing using `exifread` (primary) and `piexif` (fallback), and returns a flat `dict[str, Any]`. Returns `{}` on any parsing failure, corrupt block, or missing EXIF data. EXIF tag values must never appear in any log entry; only the exception type may be logged on failure.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: EXIF Extractor\n\n  Scenario: EXIF data is returned for an image containing metadata\n    Given raw bytes of fixtures/authentic.jpg which contains EXIF metadata\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict is non-empty\n    And the dict contains string keys corresponding to EXIF tag names\n\n  Scenario: Missing EXIF returns empty dict, not an error\n    Given raw bytes of fixtures/no_exif.jpg which contains no EXIF block\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict equals {}\n    And no exception is raised\n\n  Scenario: Corrupt EXIF block returns empty dict, not an error\n    Given raw bytes of a JPEG with a deliberately malformed EXIF header\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict equals {}\n    And no exception propagates to the caller\n\n  Scenario: EXIF values do not appear in log output\n    Given raw bytes of a JPEG with GPS coordinates in its EXIF data\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then no log entry contains the GPS coordinate values\n    And if extraction fails, the log entry contains only the exception type name\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Primary: `exifread.process_file(io.BytesIO(raw_bytes), details=False)` — returns dict of `IfdTag` objects; convert values to plain Python types (str, int, float) via `str(tag.values[0])` or similar.\n- Fallback: if `exifread` raises any exception, attempt `piexif.load(raw_bytes)` and flatten IFD dicts.\n- Outer `try/except Exception as e`: on any exception, log `WARNING f\"EXIF extraction failed: {type(e).__name__}\"` (NOT `str(e)`, which may contain tag values) and return `{}`.\n- The `details=False` flag in `exifread` suppresses thumbnail data and maker note expansion to limit memory.\n- GPS coordinates and device identifiers must not appear in any log level.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] No PII in logs — verified by capturing log output in test and asserting no GPS/device values present\n- [ ] exifread exception path tested with a crafted corrupt EXIF blob\n- [ ] piexif fallback path tested via monkeypatched exifread import\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_013Fbs13TSZxd8U3ZDjzbk65","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-011-response-assembler.md","content":"# T-011: Response Assembler\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** Response Assembler — `backend/app/assembler.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-008](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md), [T-009](T-009-heatmap-renderer.md), [T-010](T-010-exif-extractor.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-012](T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/assembler.py` — the `assemble` function that accepts a `PipelineResult`, a heatmap data URI string, and an EXIF dict, and constructs the `AnalysisResponse` Pydantic model. Validate that `score` is in `[0.0, 1.0]` and `verdict` is one of the three defined strings; clamp or correct out-of-range values and log a WARNING rather than raising. Define `AnalysisResponse`, `RegionResponse`, and `BoundingBoxResponse` Pydantic models here.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Response Assembler\n\n  Scenario: Valid pipeline result produces a well-formed AnalysisResponse\n    Given a PipelineResult with score=0.6, verdict=\"suspicious\", and 2 regions\n    And a heatmap data URI string starting with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And an exif dict {\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS\"}\n    When assemble(pipeline_result, heatmap_url, exif) is called\n    Then an AnalysisResponse is returned\n    And AnalysisResponse.score equals 0.6\n    And AnalysisResponse.verdict equals \"suspicious\"\n    And AnalysisResponse.heatmap_url starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And AnalysisResponse.exif equals {\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS\"}\n    And len(AnalysisResponse.regions) equals 2\n\n  Scenario: Out-of-range score is clamped and a WARNING is logged\n    Given a PipelineResult with score=1.5 (out of range)\n    When assemble() is called\n    Then the returned AnalysisResponse.score equals 1.0\n    And a WARNING-level log entry was emitted referencing the score clamping\n    And no exception is raised\n\n  Scenario: Empty exif dict produces AnalysisResponse with exif={}\n    Given a PipelineResult and an empty exif dict {}\n    When assemble() is called\n    Then AnalysisResponse.exif equals {}\n    And the response is otherwise valid\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `AnalysisResponse(BaseModel)`: `score: Annotated[float, Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)]`, `verdict: Literal[\"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"]`, `heatmap_url: str`, `exif: dict[str, Any]`, `regions: list[RegionResponse]`.\n- `RegionResponse(BaseModel)`: `technique: Literal[\"ELA\", \"noise_analysis\", \"clone_detection\"]`, `bounding_box: BoundingBoxResponse`, `confidence: Annotated[float, Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)]`.\n- `BoundingBoxResponse(BaseModel)`: `x: int`, `y: int`, `width: int`, `height: int`.\n- Score clamping: `score = max(0.0, min(1.0, pipeline_result.score))` before constructing model.\n- Pydantic `ValidationError` at assembly is treated as an internal error (HTTP 500) in the router.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Score clamping tested with values below 0.0 and above 1.0\n- [ ] Pydantic model serialises to correct JSON shape verified in test\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01L5JhMLGaA7qbP1Fa6Yv1So","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md","content":"# T-012: FastAPI Router & Middleware\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** FastAPI Backend — `backend/app/router.py`, `backend/app/middleware.py`, `backend/app/main.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md), [T-018](../TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the FastAPI router (`router.py`) with `POST /api/v1/analyse` and `GET /health` endpoints, the `SizeLimitMiddleware` in `middleware.py` that rejects oversized uploads before reading the full body, and wire everything together in `main.py`. Map `IngestionError` codes to HTTP status codes and `asyncio.TimeoutError` to HTTP 504. All error responses use RFC 7807 `ProblemDetails` format. CORS is configured from `Settings.cors_origins`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: FastAPI Router & Middleware\n\n  Scenario: Valid image upload returns 200 with full analysis response\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And a valid 3 MB JPEG fixture file is available\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with the file as multipart/form-data\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response Content-Type is application/json\n    And the body contains \"score\", \"verdict\", \"heatmap_url\", \"exif\", \"regions\" fields\n\n  Scenario: Upload exceeding size limit returns 413 ProblemDetails\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES is set to 1024\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with a 2 KB file\n    Then the response status is 413\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"title\" field equals \"File Too Large\"\n\n  Scenario: Analysis timeout returns 504 ProblemDetails\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS is set to 1\n    And the analysis pipeline is mocked to sleep for 5 seconds\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with a valid image\n    Then the response status is 504\n    And the response body \"title\" field equals \"Analysis Timeout\"\n\n  Scenario: Health endpoint returns 200\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When GET /health is called\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body equals {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: Route without /api/v1/ prefix returns 404\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When POST /analyse is called (without the /api/v1/ prefix)\n    Then the response status is 404\n\n  Scenario: Internal server error does not expose stack trace\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And the response assembler is mocked to raise an unexpected exception\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called\n    Then the response status is 500\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"detail\" field does not contain a file path or traceback\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `SizeLimitMiddleware` (ASGI middleware): checks `Content-Length` header; if present and > `MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES`, return 413 before reading body. If `Content-Length` absent, read in chunks and abort once threshold crossed.\n- CORS: `CORSMiddleware` with `allow_origins=settings.cors_origins`, `allow_methods=[\"POST\", \"GET\"]`, `allow_headers=[\"Content-Type\"]`.\n- `IngestionError` handler: map codes to HTTP statuses — `SIZE_EXCEEDED`→413, `UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT`→415, `MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH`→422, `DECODE_FAILED`→422.\n- `asyncio.TimeoutError` handler: HTTP 504, title `\"Analysis Timeout\"`.\n- Global `Exception` handler: HTTP 500, title `\"Internal Server Error\"`, log at ERROR level (exception type + message, no traceback in response).\n- All error responses: `Content-Type: application/problem+json`, body `{\"type\": ..., \"title\": ..., \"status\": ..., \"detail\": ...}`.\n- Tests use FastAPI `TestClient` (synchronous) from `httpx`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] All six error response shapes verified: 413, 415, 422, 504, 500, and 404\n- [ ] CORS rejection test for disallowed origin\n- [ ] No stack trace in any error response body verified in tests\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019uMFSTqtmybbAWCjwxmyZ6","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/index.md","content":"# TG-04: Frontend\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Frontend\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete React/TypeScript frontend: shared types and API client, the upload form with client-side validation, result display components (heatmap, EXIF table, region list), the application state machine and `useAnalyse` hook, and error/loading UI primitives. The frontend is fully decoupled from the backend during development via MSW service worker mocking.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md) | TypeScript Types & API Client | S | T-001 | LOW |\n| [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md) | UploadForm Component | S | T-013 | LOW |\n| [T-015](T-015-result-components.md) | Result Display Components | M | T-013 | LOW |\n| [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md) | App State Machine & useAnalyse Hook | M | T-013, T-014, T-015, T-017 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md) | ErrorBanner & LoadingSpinner | S | T-013 | LOW |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-014/T-015/T-017 in parallel): 3 days\n- Realistic (1–2 devs): 4–5 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RQaVJg5h4fM8K6n41sxLUf","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md","content":"# T-013: TypeScript Types & API Client\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/api/types.ts`, `frontend/src/api/client.ts`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-001](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md), [T-015](T-015-result-components.md), [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md), [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `frontend/src/api/types.ts` containing the TypeScript interfaces that exactly mirror the backend Pydantic models (`AnalysisResult`, `Region`, `BoundingBox`, `ProblemDetails`, `AppState`, `AppPhase`), and `frontend/src/api/client.ts` containing the `analyseImage` fetch wrapper. The client must never throw — all error paths are mapped to `AnalyseFailure`. Uses `AbortController` for timeout enforcement.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: TypeScript Types & API Client\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseSuccess on 200 response\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and returns a mock AnalysisResult JSON body with status 200\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=true\n    And outcome.data matches the AnalysisResult interface shape\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure on 4xx response\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and returns a ProblemDetails JSON body with status 422\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false\n    And outcome.title equals the title field from the ProblemDetails body\n    And outcome.status equals 422\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure on network error\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and throws a network error\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false\n    And outcome.title equals \"Service unavailable\"\n    And no exception propagates to the caller\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure when request times out\n    Given VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS is set to 100\n    And MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse with a 5 second delay\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false within 500 ms\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ExifValue = string | number | boolean | null` — no `any` for EXIF values.\n- `AnalysisResult` fields: `score: number`, `verdict: \"authentic\" | \"suspicious\" | \"likely manipulated\"`, `heatmap_url: string`, `exif: Record<string, ExifValue>`, `regions: readonly Region[]`.\n- `ProblemDetails`: `type: string`, `title: string`, `status: number`, `detail: string`.\n- `AppPhase = \"idle\" | \"uploading\" | \"analysing\" | \"result\" | \"error\"`.\n- `analyseImage`: builds `FormData` with field `\"file\"`, uses `fetch()` with `AbortController` (timeout from `import.meta.env.VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS`, default 30000).\n- On 5xx or network/abort: return `{ ok: false, title: \"Service unavailable\", status: 0 }`.\n- TypeScript `strict: true` — no implicit `any`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + MSW)\n- [ ] No `any` in type signatures — tsc strict mode passes\n- [ ] Timeout abort path tested with sub-100 ms VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DVsmPmMwrs3sHyiDUGc96r","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-014-upload-form.md","content":"# T-014: UploadForm Component\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/UploadForm.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `UploadForm` React component at `frontend/src/components/UploadForm.tsx`. The component provides a drag-and-drop zone and a file-picker input for image uploads. It enforces the client-side 10 MB size limit before calling `onFileSelected`. Accepted MIME types are `image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp, image/tiff, image/bmp`. The upload control is disabled when the `disabled` prop is `true`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: UploadForm Component\n\n  Scenario: Valid file calls onFileSelected callback\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false and a mock onFileSelected handler\n    When the user selects a 3 MB JPEG file via the file input\n    Then onFileSelected is called once with that File object\n    And no inline error message is displayed\n\n  Scenario: File exceeding 10 MB shows inline error and does not call onFileSelected\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false\n    When the user selects a 15 MB file\n    Then onFileSelected is NOT called\n    And an inline error message is displayed to the user\n    And the message does not contain an HTTP status code or stack trace\n\n  Scenario: Upload control is disabled when disabled prop is true\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=true\n    When the user attempts to interact with the file input\n    Then the input element has the disabled attribute\n    And onFileSelected is not called\n\n  Scenario: Drag-and-drop accepted file calls onFileSelected\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false\n    When the user drags and drops a valid PNG file onto the drop zone\n    Then onFileSelected is called once with the dropped File object\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `<input type=\"file\" accept=\"image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp,image/tiff,image/bmp\">` for format restriction.\n- Client-side size gate: `if (file.size > MAX_FILE_BYTES) { setError(\"File must be under 10 MB\"); return; }`.\n- `MAX_FILE_BYTES` imported from `api/client.ts`.\n- Drag events: `onDragOver`, `onDrop` on the drop zone div; `onDrop` must call `event.preventDefault()` to prevent browser default.\n- Error message rendered inline within the form (not via `ErrorBanner`).\n- The `disabled` prop disables both the `<input>` and the drag-and-drop handler.\n- TypeScript: `interface UploadFormProps { onFileSelected: (file: File) => void; disabled: boolean; }`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] Drag-and-drop tested via fireEvent.drop in tests\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01MQSC1YQHkrdNCyh4fj2vxS","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-015-result-components.md","content":"# T-015: Result Display Components\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/ResultPanel.tsx`, `HeatmapDisplay.tsx`, `ExifTable.tsx`, `RegionList.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md), [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the four result display components: `ResultPanel` (orchestrator), `HeatmapDisplay` (renders heatmap image + score badge), `ExifTable` (key/value table of EXIF metadata), and `RegionList` (annotated list of detected regions). The heatmap must render inline from the `heatmap_url` data URI. Score badge colours: green (score <= 0.3), amber (0.3 < score < 0.7), red (score >= 0.7). Empty EXIF shows a fallback message.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Result Display Components\n\n  Scenario: HeatmapDisplay renders the heatmap image inline\n    Given HeatmapDisplay is rendered with heatmapUrl=\"data:image/png;base64,abc\" and score=0.6\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then an <img> element with src=\"data:image/png;base64,abc\" is present in the DOM\n    And the browser has not navigated to a new URL\n\n  Scenario: HeatmapDisplay score badge shows amber colour for suspicious score\n    Given HeatmapDisplay is rendered with score=0.5 and verdict=\"suspicious\"\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a badge element with the amber colour class is present\n    And the badge displays the text \"suspicious\"\n\n  Scenario: ExifTable renders key-value rows for non-empty EXIF data\n    Given ExifTable is rendered with exif={\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS R\"}\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a table row with key \"Make\" and value \"Canon\" is present\n    And a table row with key \"Model\" and value \"EOS R\" is present\n\n  Scenario: ExifTable shows fallback message when EXIF is empty\n    Given ExifTable is rendered with exif={}\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then the text \"No EXIF metadata available\" is visible\n    And no table rows are rendered\n\n  Scenario: RegionList renders technique and confidence for each region\n    Given RegionList is rendered with one Region of technique=\"ELA\" and confidence=0.85\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a list item containing \"ELA\" is present\n    And a list item containing \"0.85\" or \"85%\" is present\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ResultPanel` props: `result: AnalysisResult`; composes `HeatmapDisplay`, `ExifTable`, `RegionList` without fetch logic.\n- `HeatmapDisplay` props: `heatmapUrl: string`, `score: number`, `verdict: AnalysisResult[\"verdict\"]`.\n- Badge colours via CSS classes: `score-authentic` (green), `score-suspicious` (amber), `score-manipulated` (red); class selected by score range.\n- `ExifTable` props: `exif: Record<string, ExifValue>`.\n- `RegionList` props: `regions: readonly Region[]`; renders empty state if `regions.length === 0`.\n- All components must be fully typed; no `any`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] Heatmap inline rendering verified — no navigation side-effect\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QRh43xe5BpeNkiBt8VQzxw","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-016-app-state-machine.md","content":"# T-016: App State Machine & useAnalyse Hook\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/App.tsx`, `frontend/src/hooks/useAnalyse.ts`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md), [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md), [T-015](T-015-result-components.md), [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-018](../TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `useAnalyse` hook (`hooks/useAnalyse.ts`) that manages the `AppState` phase machine (`idle → uploading → analysing → result/error`) and the top-level `App.tsx` that composes all components. The upload button must be disabled while any phase other than `idle` is active. One in-flight request per tab is enforced. The `reset()` path returns the application to `idle`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: App State Machine\n\n  Scenario: Successful analysis transitions through phases to result\n    Given the App is rendered and MSW returns a successful AnalysisResult on POST /api/v1/analyse\n    When the user selects a valid file\n    Then the phase transitions: idle -> uploading -> analysing -> result\n    And ResultPanel is rendered with the returned analysis data\n    And the upload form is no longer visible (or is disabled)\n\n  Scenario: Failed analysis transitions to error phase\n    Given the App is rendered and MSW returns a 422 ProblemDetails response\n    When the user selects a valid file\n    Then the phase transitions to error\n    And ErrorBanner is rendered with the title from the ProblemDetails response\n\n  Scenario: Upload button is disabled during analysing phase\n    Given the App is in analysing phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then the file input inside UploadForm has the disabled attribute\n\n  Scenario: Reset after result returns App to idle phase\n    Given the App is in result phase with a completed analysis\n    When the user clicks the \"Analyse another\" button\n    Then the phase returns to idle\n    And ResultPanel is no longer visible\n    And the upload form is enabled\n\n  Scenario: Second submit is ignored while analysing phase is active\n    Given the App is in analysing phase\n    When useAnalyse.submit() is called a second time\n    Then only one in-flight fetch request exists\n    And the phase does not change to uploading again\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `useAnalyse` state: `{ phase, result, error }` managed with `useState`.\n- `submit(file)`: no-op if `phase !== \"idle\"`. Sets phase to `\"uploading\"`, calls `analyseImage(file)`, sets phase to `\"analysing\"` once fetch is initiated, then transitions to `\"result\"` or `\"error\"`.\n- `reset()`: sets phase to `\"idle\"`, clears `result` and `error`.\n- Cleanup: `AbortController` must be cancelled in `useEffect` cleanup when component unmounts during in-flight request (prevent state update after unmount).\n- `App.tsx` renders: `UploadForm` (always), `LoadingSpinner` (when phase is uploading/analysing), `ResultPanel` (when phase is result), `ErrorBanner` (when phase is error).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react + MSW)\n- [ ] Phase transition sequence verified in integration test\n- [ ] Concurrent submit guard tested explicitly\n- [ ] No `any` in hook types\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_018sNjC58QiTr8nu62JRU4jy","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-017-error-loading-ui.md","content":"# T-017: ErrorBanner & LoadingSpinner\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/ErrorBanner.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/LoadingSpinner.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `ErrorBanner` and `LoadingSpinner` UI primitives. `ErrorBanner` displays a user-safe error message from the `message` prop; it must never render HTTP status codes, stack traces, or internal detail strings. `LoadingSpinner` is a simple visual indicator shown during the `uploading` and `analysing` phases.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: ErrorBanner & LoadingSpinner\n\n  Scenario: ErrorBanner renders the provided message\n    Given ErrorBanner is rendered with message=\"File Too Large\"\n    When the component is inspected\n    Then the text \"File Too Large\" is visible in the DOM\n\n  Scenario: ErrorBanner does not render internal detail strings\n    Given ErrorBanner is rendered with message=\"Service unavailable\"\n    When the component is inspected\n    Then there is no HTTP status code visible (no \"500\", \"503\", etc.)\n    And there is no stack trace text visible\n\n  Scenario: LoadingSpinner is visible during uploading phase\n    Given the App is in uploading phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then LoadingSpinner is present in the rendered output\n\n  Scenario: LoadingSpinner is not rendered in idle phase\n    Given the App is in idle phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then LoadingSpinner is not present in the rendered output\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ErrorBanner` props: `message: string` — the prop is already a user-safe string; the component just renders it.\n- `LoadingSpinner` renders an accessible `<div role=\"status\" aria-label=\"Loading\">` with a CSS spinner animation.\n- `ErrorBanner` must not expose props or logic that would allow internal strings to be rendered; the caller (App/useAnalyse) is responsible for mapping error paths to user-safe messages.\n- No third-party spinner or alert libraries; use CSS only.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] LoadingSpinner has accessible aria-label\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EkVErMuoDDKZM2DoFNXT48","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-05-integration-qa/index.md","content":"# TG-05: Integration & QA\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Integration & QA\n\n## Description\n\nDelivers the end-to-end integration test suite that exercises the complete PhotoCop stack — React frontend against the live FastAPI backend — via Docker Compose. Validates all five functional requirements through the full HTTP cycle, verifies privacy invariants (no EXIF in logs), and confirms the performance target of < 10 s for images up to 10 MB.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-018](T-018-e2e-tests.md) | End-to-End Integration Tests | M | T-012, T-016 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic: 2 days\n- Realistic: 2–3 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XNspTPiXri1aHHotfk9xg1","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md","content":"# T-018: End-to-End Integration Tests\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-05 — Integration & QA](index.md)\n- **Component:** Test suite — `backend/tests/test_router.py` (integration), optional Playwright/Cypress smoke tests\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md), [T-016](../TG-04-frontend/T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Blocks:** —\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md), [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the integration test suite in `backend/tests/test_router.py` using FastAPI's `TestClient` (and `httpx.AsyncClient` for async paths). Tests exercise the complete backend request cycle — from `POST /api/v1/analyse` with real fixture images through the full analysis pipeline — and verify all five FRs. Additional privacy invariants (no EXIF values in log output) and the performance target (< 10 s for 10 MB images) are also verified.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: End-to-End Integration Tests\n\n  Scenario: Full pipeline with authentic JPEG returns valid 200 response\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running with real (non-mocked) analysers\n    And fixtures/authentic.jpg is available (known-authentic 2 MB JPEG)\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with authentic.jpg as multipart/form-data\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body contains all five fields: score, verdict, heatmap_url, exif, regions\n    And heatmap_url starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And score is a float between 0.0 and 1.0 inclusive\n    And verdict is one of \"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"\n\n  Scenario: Oversized upload is rejected before pipeline is invoked\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And a 12 MB synthetic binary blob is available\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with the oversized file\n    Then the response status is 413\n    And the response body \"title\" equals \"File Too Large\"\n    And the analysis pipeline was never invoked\n\n  Scenario: Image with EXIF metadata returns exif dict in response\n    Given fixtures/authentic.jpg contains embedded EXIF metadata\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with authentic.jpg\n    Then the response body \"exif\" field is a non-empty JSON object\n    And the server log does not contain any EXIF tag values from that image\n\n  Scenario: PNG with no EXIF data returns exif as empty object\n    Given fixtures/no_exif.jpg is a valid JPEG with no EXIF block\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with no_exif.jpg\n    Then the response body \"exif\" field equals {}\n    And the overall response status is 200\n\n  Scenario: Analysis completes within 10 seconds for a 10 MB image\n    Given a valid 10 MB JPEG fixture is available\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with that fixture\n    Then the response is received within 10 seconds\n    And the response status is 200\n\n  Scenario: Corrupt file returns 422 without exposing internal traceback\n    Given fixtures/corrupt.bin contains invalid image bytes\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with corrupt.bin\n    Then the response status is 422\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"detail\" field does not contain a file path or Python traceback\n\n  Scenario: Health endpoint returns 200\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When GET /health is called\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body equals {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `fastapi.testclient.TestClient` for synchronous integration tests; use `httpx.AsyncClient(app=app, base_url=\"http://test\")` for async timeout tests.\n- All fixture files (`authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`) must be committed to `backend/tests/fixtures/` as part of T-001.\n- Performance test uses `time.perf_counter()` around the TestClient call; asserts elapsed < 10.0 s.\n- Log capture: use `caplog` (pytest) or `logging.handlers.MemoryHandler` to capture log lines during the EXIF privacy test; assert no GPS or device tag values appear.\n- The 10 MB fixture may be generated programmatically in the test (e.g. `PIL.Image.new(\"RGB\", (5000, 2000)).save(buf, \"JPEG\")`) to avoid committing a large binary.\n- CI requirement: tests must pass in Docker Compose environment; add a `pytest` service or run within the backend container.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] All five FRs have at least one integration test that exercises the full HTTP cycle\n- [ ] No PII in logs — verified by log capture in EXIF privacy test\n- [ ] Performance test asserts < 10 s for 10 MB image\n- [ ] Tests pass in Docker Compose CI environment\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01UsMuHALe9AZueWCMFd4RCR","tool_input":{"command":"ls /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/ && echo \"---\" && ls /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/","description":"Check if any new files were created"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_012GySgSPegzV7qx8kuBakhd","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/T-001.md","content":"# T-001: Project Scaffold & Docker Compose Setup\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md)\n- **Component:** monorepo root, Docker Compose\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** —\n- **Blocks:** T-002, T-003, T-013\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nCreate the complete monorepo directory structure for PhotoCop, including the `backend/` Python project, the `frontend/` Vite/React/TypeScript project, the `docker-compose.yml` for development, and all project-level configuration files (`.env.example`, `.gitignore`, dependency manifests). No implementation logic is written in this task — only the scaffold that gives every subsequent task a valid place to work.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Project Scaffold\n\n  Scenario: Docker Compose starts both services successfully\n    Given the repository root contains a valid docker-compose.yml\n    When a developer runs docker compose up --build\n    Then both backend (port 8000) and frontend (port 5173) containers start without errors\n    And the backend healthcheck passes within 30 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Backend stub health endpoint responds\n    Given the Docker Compose stack is running\n    When a client sends GET http://localhost:8000/health\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body is {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: TypeScript strict mode is enforced\n    Given frontend/tsconfig.json exists\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains \"strict\": true\n    And it contains \"noImplicitAny\": true\n\n  Scenario: All required environment variables are documented\n    Given .env.example exists in the repository root\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains entries for MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES, ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, CORS_ORIGINS, ELA_WEIGHT, NOISE_WEIGHT, CLONE_WEIGHT, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED, HEATMAP_ALPHA\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `pyproject.toml` must declare runtime deps: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `pydantic>=2`, `pydantic-settings`, `pillow`, `numpy`, `opencv-python-headless`, `scikit-image`, `python-magic`, `filetype`, `exifread`, `piexif`.\n- `frontend/package.json` must declare: `react@^18`, `react-dom@^18`, `typescript`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`, `msw`.\n- `backend/tests/fixtures/` directory must contain placeholder files `authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`.\n- Docker healthcheck: `curl -f http://localhost:8000/health`, interval 30s, timeout 5s, retries 3.\n- `.gitignore` must exclude `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env`, `dist/`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] `docker compose up --build` succeeds end-to-end\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`\n- [ ] `.env.example` documents all environment variables from L1/L2 design\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DXQtr5C3xZF28NRQtotmAw","tool_input":{"command":"cat > specs/plan-tasks/plan.md << 'ENDOFFILE'\n# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\nENDOFFILE\necho \"Done writing plan.md\"","description":"Write plan.md using bash heredoc"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_017YAqBKU6rwk8uu6S4KUFEg","tool_input":{"command":"cat > /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md << 'ENDOFFILE'\ntest\nENDOFFILE\necho $?","description":"Test writing to plan.md via cat"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PZJSnpVrte2grLcDpTXkA3","tool_input":{"command":"printf 'test\\n' > plan.md && echo \"success\" || echo \"failed\"","description":"Test write from project root using relative path"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01YQEG8xupi4vk8LEoHEXzd3","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport os\nos.makedirs('specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold', exist_ok=True)\nwith open('specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md', 'w') as f:\n    f.write('# TG-01 test\\n')\nprint('success')\n\"","description":"Test writing via Python subprocess"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tm3oF9Vxo1aUHdjdetCPtu","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"print('hello')\"","description":"Test Python execution"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01HXiDFvwKkeb5wMMHn9sPF9","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01B52xm5yp9RsktdRdgGXsqY","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/index.md","content":"# Implementation Tasks\n\n| Group | Title | Tasks | Total Effort | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| [TG-01](TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md) | Infrastructure & Scaffold | 2 tasks | ~2 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-02](TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md) | Backend Analysis Pipeline | 6 tasks | ~12 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-03](TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md) | Backend API & Output | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-04](TG-04-frontend/index.md) | Frontend | 5 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-05](TG-05-integration-qa/index.md) | Integration & QA | 1 task | ~2 days | PENDING |\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AXMrNgcNW4A12GskAxJEbH","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md","content":"# TG-01: Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n## Description\n\nEstablishes the monorepo directory layout, Docker Compose development environment, Python and Node.js dependency manifests, and all project-level configuration files. This group delivers the skeleton that every other task depends on.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md) | Project Scaffold & Docker Compose | M | — | LOW |\n| [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md) | Backend Config & App Factory | S | T-001 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (full parallel): 1 day\n- Realistic (1 dev, sequential): 2 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01M8cMacu4JFAMJm257y19oW","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md","content":"# T-001: Project Scaffold & Docker Compose\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** monorepo root, Docker Compose\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** —\n- **Blocks:** [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md), [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nCreate the complete monorepo directory structure for PhotoCop: the `backend/` Python project, the `frontend/` Vite/React/TypeScript project, the `docker-compose.yml` for development, and all project-level configuration files (`.env.example`, `.gitignore`, dependency manifests). No implementation logic is included — only the scaffold that gives every subsequent task a valid working directory.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Project Scaffold\n\n  Scenario: Docker Compose starts both services successfully\n    Given the repository root contains a valid docker-compose.yml\n    When a developer runs docker compose up --build\n    Then both backend (port 8000) and frontend (port 5173) containers start without errors\n    And the backend healthcheck passes within 30 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Backend stub health endpoint responds\n    Given the Docker Compose stack is running\n    When a client sends GET http://localhost:8000/health\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body is {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: TypeScript strict mode is enforced in tsconfig\n    Given frontend/tsconfig.json exists\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains \"strict\": true\n    And it contains \"noImplicitAny\": true\n\n  Scenario: All required environment variables are documented\n    Given .env.example exists in the repository root\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains entries for MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES, ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, CORS_ORIGINS, ELA_WEIGHT, NOISE_WEIGHT, CLONE_WEIGHT, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED, HEATMAP_ALPHA\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `pyproject.toml` must declare runtime deps: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `pydantic>=2`, `pydantic-settings`, `pillow`, `numpy`, `opencv-python-headless`, `scikit-image`, `python-magic`, `filetype`, `exifread`, `piexif`.\n- `frontend/package.json` must declare: `react@^18`, `react-dom@^18`, `typescript`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`, `msw`.\n- `backend/tests/fixtures/` directory must contain placeholder files `authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`.\n- Docker healthcheck: `curl -f http://localhost:8000/health`, interval 30s, timeout 5s, retries 3.\n- `.gitignore` must exclude `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env`, `dist/`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] `docker compose up --build` succeeds end-to-end\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`\n- [ ] `.env.example` documents all environment variables from L1/L2 design\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019XpFboXs7H5pBr1N5viof7","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md","content":"# T-002: Backend Config & App Factory\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** FastAPI Backend — `config.py`, `main.py`, `errors.py`, `dependencies.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the Pydantic `Settings` model (`config.py`), the FastAPI application factory (`main.py`), the global exception handler producing RFC 7807 `ProblemDetails` responses (`errors.py`), and the `get_settings` dependency factory (`dependencies.py`). The `Settings` model must validate at startup that `ELA_WEIGHT + NOISE_WEIGHT + CLONE_WEIGHT == 1.0`; a misconfigured environment must cause a hard startup failure with a clear error message.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Backend Config & App Factory\n\n  Scenario: Settings load from environment variables with correct defaults\n    Given no environment variables are set\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then max_upload_bytes equals 10485760\n    And analysis_timeout_seconds equals 9\n    And cors_origins contains \"http://localhost:5173\"\n\n  Scenario: Settings validation rejects weights that do not sum to 1.0\n    Given ELA_WEIGHT=0.5 and NOISE_WEIGHT=0.3 and CLONE_WEIGHT=0.3 are set in the environment\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then a ValidationError is raised\n    And the error message references the weight sum constraint\n\n  Scenario: Unhandled exception produces RFC 7807 ProblemDetails response\n    Given the FastAPI application is running\n    When a request triggers an unhandled internal exception\n    Then the response status is 500\n    And the Content-Type header is application/problem+json\n    And the response body contains \"type\", \"title\", \"status\", \"detail\" fields\n    And the \"detail\" field does not contain a Python traceback or internal file path\n\n  Scenario: CORS allows configured origin\n    Given CORS_ORIGINS is set to http://localhost:5173\n    When a preflight OPTIONS request arrives from http://localhost:5173\n    Then the response includes Access-Control-Allow-Origin for that origin\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings` for `Settings`; all env var aliases match the names in `.env.example`.\n- `@model_validator(mode=\"after\")` on `Settings` checks weight sum; tolerance of 1e-6 acceptable for float arithmetic.\n- `python-magic` requires OS-level `libmagic1`; Dockerfile must include `apt-get install -y libmagic1`. Missing library causes `ImportError` at startup, not at request time.\n- Global exception handler must log the internal exception at ERROR level (exception type + message) but must never include the traceback in the HTTP response body.\n- `get_settings` uses `@lru_cache()` so Settings is a singleton per process.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Weight sum validator tested with both valid and invalid float combinations\n- [ ] RFC 7807 response shape verified by test against actual exception handler\n- [ ] No PII in logs (EXIF values must never appear)\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EJuTMEBqPwHVvW7hCVrKgv","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md","content":"# TG-02: Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete forensic image analysis pipeline: Image Ingestion Service (magic-byte validation and PIL decoding), the three forensic analysers (ELA, Noise, Clone Detection), the Score Aggregator, and the Analysis Engine orchestrator that fans out to the analysers concurrently. This group delivers the core intelligence of PhotoCop.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md) | Image Ingestion Service | M | T-002 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md) | ELA Analyser | M | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md) | Noise Analyser | M | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md) | Clone Detector | L | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md) | Score Aggregator | S | T-004, T-005, T-006 | LOW |\n| [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md) | Analysis Engine Orchestrator | M | T-007 | HIGH |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-004/T-005/T-006 in parallel after T-003): 5 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 8–10 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_012ZPSUsPYDafdJw1NmwhFCp","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md","content":"# T-003: Image Ingestion Service\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Image Ingestion Service — `backend/app/ingestion.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-002](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md), [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md), [T-010](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-010-exif-extractor.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `ImageBuffer` dataclass and the `ingest` function in `backend/app/ingestion.py`. The function reads raw bytes from the FastAPI `UploadFile`, validates the file size, performs magic-byte detection using `python-magic` (with `filetype` as pure-Python fallback), decodes the validated bytes into a normalised PIL `Image`, and returns an `ImageBuffer`. All error paths raise a typed `IngestionError` with a `code` field that the API router maps to the correct HTTP status.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Image Ingestion Service\n\n  Scenario: Valid JPEG is accepted and decoded\n    Given raw bytes of a 3 MB valid JPEG file\n    When ingest() is called with those bytes and content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an ImageBuffer is returned\n    And ImageBuffer.format equals \"JPEG\"\n    And ImageBuffer.image is a PIL Image in RGB or RGBA mode\n    And ImageBuffer.raw_bytes equals the original input bytes\n\n  Scenario: File exceeding size limit raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a file with size greater than MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"SIZE_EXCEEDED\"\n\n  Scenario: File with mismatched magic bytes raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a PDF file renamed with .jpg extension\n    When ingest() is called with content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\"\n\n  Scenario: Unsupported format GIF raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes of a valid GIF image\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\"\n\n  Scenario: Truncated image bytes raises IngestionError\n    Given raw bytes with valid JPEG magic bytes but truncated binary content\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"DECODE_FAILED\"\n\n  Scenario: No data is written to disk at any point\n    Given valid image bytes are provided to ingest()\n    When ingest() completes successfully or with failure\n    Then no new files are created in the filesystem\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `python-magic` for magic-byte detection; fall back to `filetype` if `python-magic` import fails (libmagic not installed). Never use `imghdr` (removed in Python 3.13).\n- Supported magic signatures: JPEG (`FF D8 FF`), PNG (`89 50 4E 47`), WebP (`52 49 46 46...57 45 42 50`), TIFF (`49 49 2A 00` or `4D 4D 00 2A`), BMP (`42 4D`).\n- `ImageBuffer` is a `@dataclass` with fields: `image: PIL.Image.Image`, `raw_bytes: bytes`, `format: str`, `size_bytes: int`.\n- `IngestionError` carries a `code: Literal[\"SIZE_EXCEEDED\", \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\", \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\", \"DECODE_FAILED\"]` field.\n- PIL decoding: open from `io.BytesIO(raw_bytes)`, call `image.convert(\"RGB\")` for non-alpha formats.\n- Security: never write to disk; never execute uploaded bytes.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Tests use fixture files: `corrupt.bin`, `authentic.jpg`, `no_exif.jpg`, plus a synthetic oversized blob\n- [ ] No PII in logs (raw bytes must never be logged)\n- [ ] `python-magic` fallback to `filetype` tested via monkeypatched import\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_014eLrQYn3HD4egSABuVhjVA","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-004-ela-analyser.md","content":"# T-004: ELA Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the ELA (Error Level Analysis) forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`. The analyser re-saves the image at a known JPEG quality level, computes the absolute pixel difference between original and re-saved versions, amplifies the result, and identifies high-anomaly zones as `RegionResult` objects. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"ELA\"`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: ELA Analyser\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"ELA\"\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns elevated sub-score for a known-manipulated image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/manipulated.png as a read-only copy\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions is a non-empty list\n\n  Scenario: ELA does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: ELA handles a heavily-compressed JPEG without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image of a highly compressed JPEG with quality below 30\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n    And sub_score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n\n  Scenario: ELA with invalid quality parameter raises ValueError\n    Given a valid PIL Image\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=0) is called\n    Then a ValueError is raised\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Re-save to `io.BytesIO` at specified quality using `PIL.Image.save(buf, format=\"JPEG\", quality=quality)`.\n- Amplify difference: `diff = ImageChops.difference(original, resaved)`; scale to `[0, 255]` range.\n- Identify high-anomaly zones: threshold at mean + 2*std of the difference map; connected-component labelling via `skimage.measure.label`.\n- Each connected component above minimum area becomes a `RegionResult` with `technique=\"ELA\"`.\n- `confidence` per region = normalised mean ELA value in that region, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Sub-score = proportion of pixels above threshold, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Never write intermediate buffers to disk.\n- Quality parameter valid range: 1–95 (raise `ValueError` outside range).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified by pixel comparison test\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all test paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PupnWJYrgZkGpzdGfLxpnT","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-005-noise-analyser.md","content":"# T-005: Noise Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the noise-inconsistency forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`. The analyser computes a noise residual map by subtracting a Gaussian-filtered version of the image from the original, then identifies regions with statistically anomalous noise variance. Inconsistent noise patterns indicate splicing or copy-paste manipulation. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"noise_analysis\"`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Noise Analyser\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"noise_analysis\"\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser detects inconsistency in a spliced image\n    Given a PIL Image constructed by pasting a region from a different image\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions contains at least one entry whose bounding_box overlaps the pasted region\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser handles a grayscale image without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image in mode \"L\" (grayscale)\n    When noise_analyse(image) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Convert image to grayscale numpy array before filtering.\n- Apply `scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter` (sigma configurable, default 2) to produce denoised version.\n- Residual = `original_gray - denoised_gray` (absolute values).\n- Compute local variance using sliding window (`skimage.filters.rank.variance` or manual convolution).\n- Regions with local variance > mean + 2*std are flagged.\n- Connected-component labelling via `skimage.measure.label`; each component above minimum area becomes a `RegionResult`.\n- Sub-score = proportion of pixels above variance threshold, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Input image must not be mutated; work on a copy.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01VuH9zoYaswKEmDXBsB83DC","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-006-clone-detector.md","content":"# T-006: Clone Detector\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** L\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement copy-move forgery detection in `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`. The detector computes ORB keypoint descriptors, clusters matched descriptor pairs, and identifies spatially distinct image patches that share high-confidence descriptor matches — evidence of copy-move forgery. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"clone_detection\"`. Images must be downsampled to at most 1024 px on the longest edge before descriptor computation to stay within the performance budget.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Clone Detector\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.3\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"clone_detection\"\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector identifies copy-moved regions\n    Given a PIL Image with a known duplicated region where one quadrant is copied from another\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions contains at least two entries\n    And the bounding boxes of those entries are spatially non-adjacent\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector completes within time budget for a 10 MB image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from a 10 MB JPEG fixture\n    When clone_detect(image) is called\n    Then the function returns within 3 seconds\n    And an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns empty regions when no matches exceed threshold\n    Given a PIL Image with no duplicate regions\n    When clone_detect(image, min_match_threshold=10) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.regions is an empty list\n    And AnalyserOutput.sub_score equals 0.0\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Downsample image to max 1024 px longest edge before ORB computation using `PIL.Image.thumbnail` (aspect-ratio preserving).\n- Use `cv2.ORB_create(nfeatures=1000)` for descriptor extraction.\n- Match descriptors with `cv2.BFMatcher(cv2.NORM_HAMMING)` and apply ratio test (Lowe's ratio 0.75).\n- Cluster matched pairs; spatially distinct pairs (centroid distance > 10% of image dimension) are copy-move candidates.\n- Scale bounding boxes back to original image coordinates after detection at downsampled resolution.\n- Sub-score = number of confirmed clone pairs / (number of clone pairs + 10), clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- `min_match_threshold` parameter (default 5): minimum matching descriptors to declare a clone.\n- Never mutate input image; always work on a downsampled copy.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Performance test with 10 MB fixture confirms completion in < 3 s\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01KRXg3mGMtDoPU5H546STW3","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-007-score-aggregator.md","content":"# T-007: Score Aggregator\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py` containing the `aggregate` function that accepts three `AnalyserOutput` objects, computes a weighted average score, derives the verdict string from configurable thresholds, and merges all region lists into a `PipelineResult`. Weights and thresholds are read from `Settings`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Score Aggregator\n\n  Scenario: Weighted average score is computed correctly\n    Given ELA sub-score 0.8 and noise sub-score 0.2 and clone sub-score 0.0\n    And weights ELA=0.4 and noise=0.3 and clone=0.3\n    When aggregate() is called with these outputs\n    Then the returned PipelineResult.score equals 0.38 within a tolerance of 1e-6\n\n  Scenario: Score in range 0.0 to 0.3 produces \"authentic\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.2 produced by aggregate()\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"authentic\"\n\n  Scenario: Score in range 0.3 to 0.7 exclusive produces \"suspicious\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.5 produced by aggregate()\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"suspicious\"\n\n  Scenario: Score in range 0.7 to 1.0 produces \"likely manipulated\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.85 produced by aggregate()\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"likely manipulated\"\n\n  Scenario: All regions from all analysers appear in the merged output\n    Given ELA returns 2 regions and clone returns 1 region and noise returns 0 regions\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.regions contains exactly 3 entries\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `PipelineResult` is a `@dataclass` with `score: float`, `verdict: str`, `regions: list[RegionResult]`.\n- Score = `ela_weight * ela_score + noise_weight * noise_score + clone_weight * clone_score`.\n- Verdict thresholds from `Settings.verdict_threshold_authentic` (default 0.3) and `Settings.verdict_threshold_manipulated` (default 0.7).\n- Region list = concatenation of all three region lists; no deduplication needed (different `technique` fields).\n- Score is clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]` after computation as a defensive guard.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Score boundary conditions tested at exactly 0.3 and 0.7\n- [ ] Region count verified in all three-analyser combinations\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gu7fhBngZHWP1zh5jEdBfR","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md","content":"# T-008: Analysis Engine Orchestrator\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/engine.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-009](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-009-heatmap-renderer.md), [T-011](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-011-response-assembler.md), [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/analysis/engine.py` — the `run_pipeline` async function that receives an `ImageBuffer`, fans out to all three analysers concurrently using `asyncio.gather` over a `ThreadPoolExecutor`, collects `AnalyserOutput` objects, passes them to the `ScoreAggregator`, and returns a `PipelineResult`. Each analyser receives an independent `Image.copy()` to guarantee read-only isolation. The outer function enforces the `ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` hard limit via `asyncio.wait_for`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Analysis Engine Orchestrator\n\n  Scenario: All three analysers are called and results aggregated\n    Given an ImageBuffer containing a valid PIL Image\n    And mock implementations of ela_analyse, noise_analyse, and clone_detect are injected\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then all three mock analysers were called exactly once\n    And run_pipeline returns a PipelineResult with score and verdict populated\n\n  Scenario: Each analyser receives a distinct copy of the image\n    Given an ImageBuffer containing a PIL Image\n    And spy wrappers around each analyser that record the Python object id of the image received\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then each analyser received a different Python object id\n    And the original ImageBuffer.image object id was not passed directly to any analyser\n\n  Scenario: Analysis timeout raises asyncio.TimeoutError\n    Given an ImageBuffer and ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS set to 1\n    And a mock ELA analyser that sleeps for 5 seconds\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called\n    Then asyncio.TimeoutError is raised within 2 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Pipeline result contains valid score range\n    Given an ImageBuffer loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    When run_pipeline(image_buffer) is called with real analysers\n    Then a PipelineResult is returned\n    And PipelineResult.score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n    And PipelineResult.verdict is one of \"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `run_pipeline` is `async def`; analysers run in `loop.run_in_executor(executor, analyser_fn, image_copy)`.\n- Use `ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=3)` created at module level (not per-request).\n- `asyncio.gather` with `return_exceptions=False` so any analyser exception propagates immediately.\n- `asyncio.wait_for(gather_coro, timeout=settings.analysis_timeout_seconds)` enforces the hard limit.\n- Image copies: one `Image.copy()` per analyser before dispatch.\n- On `asyncio.TimeoutError`: let it propagate to the router, which maps it to HTTP 504.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Image copy isolation verified by object identity test\n- [ ] Timeout behaviour tested with a slow mock analyser\n- [ ] No shared mutable state between concurrent calls verified\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01YMJF7wcAy7Ji2wfjYycwWr","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md","content":"# TG-03: Backend API & Output\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend API & Output\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the four output-facing backend components: Heatmap Renderer (coloured overlay as base64 data URI), EXIF Extractor (privacy-safe metadata parsing), Response Assembler (Pydantic `AnalysisResponse` model), and the FastAPI Router with middleware, error handlers, and CORS configuration. This group delivers the complete, runnable backend API.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-009](T-009-heatmap-renderer.md) | Heatmap Renderer | M | T-008 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-010](T-010-exif-extractor.md) | EXIF Extractor | S | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md) | Response Assembler | S | T-008, T-009, T-010 | LOW |\n| [T-012](T-012-fastapi-router.md) | FastAPI Router & Middleware | M | T-011 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-009 and T-010 in parallel): 3 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 4–5 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019s5HmoMdfmpyB8FqFfwgD7","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-009-heatmap-renderer.md","content":"# T-009: Heatmap Renderer\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** Heatmap Renderer — `backend/app/heatmap.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-008](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/heatmap.py` — the `render` function that composites a colour-coded overlay of `RegionResult` bounding boxes onto the original PIL image and returns the result as a `data:image/png;base64,...` data URI string. High-confidence regions are rendered red, low-confidence regions yellow-green. On empty regions list, returns the original image as a data URI unchanged. If compositing fails for any region, logs a WARNING and continues without that region.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Heatmap Renderer\n\n  Scenario: Non-empty regions produce a data URI with overlay\n    Given a PIL Image and a list containing one RegionResult at confidence 0.9\n    When render(image, regions, alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then the returned string starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And the base64-decoded bytes represent a valid PNG image\n\n  Scenario: Empty regions list returns the original image as data URI\n    Given a PIL Image and an empty regions list\n    When render(image, regions=[], alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then the returned string starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And the decoded PNG has the same dimensions as the original image\n\n  Scenario: Renderer does not write any files to disk\n    Given a PIL Image and any regions list\n    When render() is called\n    Then no new files are created in the filesystem\n\n  Scenario: Malformed bounding box is skipped with a WARNING log not an exception\n    Given a PIL Image and a RegionResult with bounding_box x=-1 y=-1 width=-1 height=-1\n    When render(image, regions, alpha=0.5) is called\n    Then a valid data URI is returned\n    And a WARNING-level log entry was emitted\n    And the WARNING message does not contain image pixel data\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `PIL.Image`, `PIL.ImageDraw` for overlay compositing.\n- Colour map: `confidence` 0.0 maps to yellow-green (R=180, G=255, B=0), `confidence` 1.0 maps to red (R=255, G=0, B=0). Linear interpolation.\n- Alpha parameter (default 0.5, read from `Settings.heatmap_alpha`): controls overlay opacity.\n- Composite using `PIL.Image.blend` or `paste` with an RGBA mask.\n- Encode to PNG via `io.BytesIO`; encode with `base64.b64encode`; prepend `\"data:image/png;base64,\"`.\n- Never write to disk; release all intermediate PIL objects after data URI is produced.\n- On `IndexError` or `ValueError` from malformed bounding box: log `WARNING \"Heatmap: skipping malformed region\"` (no pixel data in message) and continue.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] No PII in logs (no pixel data, no EXIF values)\n- [ ] Output is always a valid base64-encoded PNG verified by decoding in test\n- [ ] No disk writes verified by filesystem state check in test\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01FsHn32u5Yw8zKCRM5aEqCZ","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-010-exif-extractor.md","content":"# T-010: EXIF Extractor\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** EXIF Extractor — `backend/app/exif.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/exif.py` — the `extract` function that accepts raw image bytes, attempts EXIF parsing using `exifread` (primary) and `piexif` (fallback), and returns a flat `dict[str, Any]`. Returns `{}` on any parsing failure, corrupt block, or missing EXIF data. EXIF tag values must never appear in any log entry; only the exception type may be logged on failure.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: EXIF Extractor\n\n  Scenario: EXIF data is returned for an image containing metadata\n    Given raw bytes of fixtures/authentic.jpg which contains EXIF metadata\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict is non-empty\n    And the dict contains string keys corresponding to EXIF tag names\n\n  Scenario: Missing EXIF returns empty dict not an error\n    Given raw bytes of fixtures/no_exif.jpg which contains no EXIF block\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict equals {}\n    And no exception is raised\n\n  Scenario: Corrupt EXIF block returns empty dict not an error\n    Given raw bytes of a JPEG with a deliberately malformed EXIF header\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then the returned dict equals {}\n    And no exception propagates to the caller\n\n  Scenario: EXIF values do not appear in log output on failure\n    Given raw bytes of a JPEG with GPS coordinates in its EXIF data\n    And the exifread library raises an exception during parsing\n    When extract(raw_bytes) is called\n    Then no log entry contains the GPS coordinate values\n    And if extraction fails the log entry contains only the exception type name\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Primary: `exifread.process_file(io.BytesIO(raw_bytes), details=False)` — convert `IfdTag` values to plain Python types.\n- Fallback: if `exifread` raises, attempt `piexif.load(raw_bytes)` and flatten IFD dicts.\n- Outer `try/except Exception as e`: on any exception, log `WARNING f\"EXIF extraction failed: {type(e).__name__}\"` (NOT `str(e)`, which may contain tag values) and return `{}`.\n- The `details=False` flag in `exifread` suppresses thumbnail data and maker note expansion.\n- GPS coordinates and device identifiers must not appear in any log level.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] No PII in logs — verified by capturing log output in test and asserting no GPS/device values present\n- [ ] exifread exception path tested with a crafted corrupt EXIF blob\n- [ ] piexif fallback path tested via monkeypatched exifread import\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DNaqEAuEwr7AH6R9kQvu3A","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-011-response-assembler.md","content":"# T-011: Response Assembler\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** Response Assembler — `backend/app/assembler.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-008](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-008-analysis-engine.md), [T-009](T-009-heatmap-renderer.md), [T-010](T-010-exif-extractor.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-012](T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/assembler.py` — the `assemble` function that accepts a `PipelineResult`, a heatmap data URI string, and an EXIF dict, and constructs the `AnalysisResponse` Pydantic model. Validate that `score` is in `[0.0, 1.0]` and `verdict` is one of the three defined strings; clamp or correct out-of-range values and log a WARNING. Define `AnalysisResponse`, `RegionResponse`, and `BoundingBoxResponse` Pydantic models in this module.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Response Assembler\n\n  Scenario: Valid pipeline result produces a well-formed AnalysisResponse\n    Given a PipelineResult with score=0.6 and verdict=\"suspicious\" and 2 regions\n    And a heatmap data URI string starting with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And an exif dict {\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS\"}\n    When assemble(pipeline_result, heatmap_url, exif) is called\n    Then an AnalysisResponse is returned\n    And AnalysisResponse.score equals 0.6\n    And AnalysisResponse.verdict equals \"suspicious\"\n    And AnalysisResponse.heatmap_url starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And AnalysisResponse.exif equals {\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS\"}\n    And len(AnalysisResponse.regions) equals 2\n\n  Scenario: Out-of-range score is clamped and a WARNING is logged\n    Given a PipelineResult with score=1.5 which is out of range\n    When assemble() is called\n    Then the returned AnalysisResponse.score equals 1.0\n    And a WARNING-level log entry was emitted referencing the score clamping\n    And no exception is raised\n\n  Scenario: Empty exif dict produces valid AnalysisResponse\n    Given a PipelineResult and an empty exif dict {}\n    When assemble() is called\n    Then AnalysisResponse.exif equals {}\n    And the overall response is otherwise valid\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `AnalysisResponse(BaseModel)`: `score: Annotated[float, Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)]`, `verdict: Literal[\"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"]`, `heatmap_url: str`, `exif: dict[str, Any]`, `regions: list[RegionResponse]`.\n- `RegionResponse(BaseModel)`: `technique: Literal[\"ELA\", \"noise_analysis\", \"clone_detection\"]`, `bounding_box: BoundingBoxResponse`, `confidence: Annotated[float, Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)]`.\n- `BoundingBoxResponse(BaseModel)`: `x: int`, `y: int`, `width: int`, `height: int`.\n- Score clamping: `score = max(0.0, min(1.0, pipeline_result.score))` before constructing model.\n- Pydantic `ValidationError` at assembly propagates as HTTP 500 in the router.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Score clamping tested with values below 0.0 and above 1.0\n- [ ] Pydantic model serialises to correct JSON shape verified in test\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_011yYTmPMj6stXSRGHDNQbWC","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md","content":"# T-012: FastAPI Router & Middleware\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-03 — Backend API & Output](index.md)\n- **Component:** FastAPI Backend — `backend/app/router.py`, `backend/app/middleware.py`, `backend/app/main.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-011](T-011-response-assembler.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md), [T-018](../TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the FastAPI router (`router.py`) with `POST /api/v1/analyse` and `GET /health` endpoints, the `SizeLimitMiddleware` in `middleware.py` that rejects oversized uploads before reading the full body, and wire everything together in `main.py`. Map `IngestionError` codes to HTTP status codes and `asyncio.TimeoutError` to HTTP 504. All error responses use RFC 7807 `ProblemDetails` format. CORS is configured from `Settings.cors_origins`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: FastAPI Router & Middleware\n\n  Scenario: Valid image upload returns 200 with full analysis response\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And a valid 3 MB JPEG fixture file is available\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with the file as multipart/form-data\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response Content-Type is application/json\n    And the body contains \"score\", \"verdict\", \"heatmap_url\", \"exif\", \"regions\" fields\n\n  Scenario: Upload exceeding size limit returns 413 ProblemDetails\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES is set to 1024\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with a 2 KB file\n    Then the response status is 413\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"title\" field equals \"File Too Large\"\n\n  Scenario: Analysis timeout returns 504 ProblemDetails\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS is set to 1\n    And the analysis pipeline is mocked to sleep for 5 seconds\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with a valid image\n    Then the response status is 504\n    And the response body \"title\" field equals \"Analysis Timeout\"\n\n  Scenario: Health endpoint returns 200\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When GET /health is called\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body equals {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: Route without /api/v1/ prefix returns 404\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When POST /analyse is called without the /api/v1/ prefix\n    Then the response status is 404\n\n  Scenario: Internal server error does not expose stack trace\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And the response assembler is mocked to raise an unexpected exception\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with a valid image\n    Then the response status is 500\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"detail\" field does not contain a Python file path or traceback\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `SizeLimitMiddleware` (ASGI middleware): checks `Content-Length` header; if present and > `MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES`, return 413 before reading body.\n- CORS: `CORSMiddleware` with `allow_origins=settings.cors_origins`, `allow_methods=[\"POST\", \"GET\"]`, `allow_headers=[\"Content-Type\"]`.\n- `IngestionError` handler: `SIZE_EXCEEDED`→413, `UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT`→415, `MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH`→422, `DECODE_FAILED`→422.\n- `asyncio.TimeoutError` handler: HTTP 504, title `\"Analysis Timeout\"`.\n- Global `Exception` handler: HTTP 500, title `\"Internal Server Error\"`, log at ERROR level (exception type + message, no traceback in response).\n- All error responses: `Content-Type: application/problem+json`, body `{\"type\": ..., \"title\": ..., \"status\": ..., \"detail\": ...}`.\n- Tests use FastAPI `TestClient` from `httpx`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] All six error response shapes verified: 413, 415, 422, 504, 500, and 404\n- [ ] CORS rejection test for disallowed origin\n- [ ] No stack trace in any error response body verified in tests\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01FJ6tqiWLpLp4Urz4ZcGar4","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/index.md","content":"# TG-04: Frontend\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Frontend\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete React/TypeScript frontend: shared types and API client, the upload form with client-side validation, result display components (heatmap, EXIF table, region list), the application state machine and `useAnalyse` hook, and error/loading UI primitives. The frontend is fully decoupled from the backend during development via MSW service worker mocking.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md) | TypeScript Types & API Client | S | T-001 | LOW |\n| [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md) | UploadForm Component | S | T-013 | LOW |\n| [T-015](T-015-result-components.md) | Result Display Components | M | T-013 | LOW |\n| [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md) | App State Machine & useAnalyse Hook | M | T-013, T-014, T-015, T-017 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md) | ErrorBanner & LoadingSpinner | S | T-013 | LOW |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-014/T-015/T-017 in parallel): 3 days\n- Realistic (1–2 devs): 4–5 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DzbhvL35FgAxq9C6xPhQxV","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md","content":"# T-013: TypeScript Types & API Client\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/api/types.ts`, `frontend/src/api/client.ts`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-001](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md), [T-015](T-015-result-components.md), [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md), [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `frontend/src/api/types.ts` containing the TypeScript interfaces that exactly mirror the backend Pydantic models (`AnalysisResult`, `Region`, `BoundingBox`, `ProblemDetails`, `AppState`, `AppPhase`), and `frontend/src/api/client.ts` containing the `analyseImage` fetch wrapper. The client must never throw — all error paths are mapped to `AnalyseFailure`. Uses `AbortController` for timeout enforcement.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: TypeScript Types & API Client\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseSuccess on 200 response\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and returns a mock AnalysisResult JSON body with status 200\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=true\n    And outcome.data matches the AnalysisResult interface shape\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure on 4xx response\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and returns a ProblemDetails JSON body with status 422\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false\n    And outcome.title equals the title field from the ProblemDetails body\n    And outcome.status equals 422\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure on network error\n    Given MSW intercepts POST /api/v1/analyse and throws a network error\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false\n    And outcome.title equals \"Service unavailable\"\n    And no exception propagates to the caller\n\n  Scenario: analyseImage resolves to AnalyseFailure when request times out\n    Given VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS is set to 100\n    And MSW delays the POST /api/v1/analyse response by 5 seconds\n    When analyseImage(mockFile) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyseOutcome has ok=false within 500 ms\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ExifValue = string | number | boolean | null` — no `any` for EXIF values.\n- `AnalysisResult` fields: `score: number`, `verdict: \"authentic\" | \"suspicious\" | \"likely manipulated\"`, `heatmap_url: string`, `exif: Record<string, ExifValue>`, `regions: readonly Region[]`.\n- `ProblemDetails`: `type: string`, `title: string`, `status: number`, `detail: string`.\n- `AppPhase = \"idle\" | \"uploading\" | \"analysing\" | \"result\" | \"error\"`.\n- `analyseImage`: builds `FormData` with field `\"file\"`, uses `fetch()` with `AbortController` (timeout from `import.meta.env.VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS`, default 30000).\n- On 5xx or network/abort: return `{ ok: false, title: \"Service unavailable\", status: 0 }`.\n- TypeScript `strict: true` — no implicit `any`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + MSW)\n- [ ] No `any` in type signatures — tsc strict mode passes with zero errors\n- [ ] Timeout abort path tested with sub-100 ms VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_012tSbopmvgNmAmBFNFwRRgp","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-014-upload-form.md","content":"# T-014: UploadForm Component\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/UploadForm.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `UploadForm` React component at `frontend/src/components/UploadForm.tsx`. The component provides a drag-and-drop zone and a file-picker input for image uploads. It enforces the client-side 10 MB size limit before calling `onFileSelected`. Accepted MIME types are `image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp, image/tiff, image/bmp`. The upload control is disabled when the `disabled` prop is `true`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: UploadForm Component\n\n  Scenario: Valid file calls onFileSelected callback\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false and a mock onFileSelected handler\n    When the user selects a 3 MB JPEG file via the file input\n    Then onFileSelected is called once with that File object\n    And no inline error message is displayed\n\n  Scenario: File exceeding 10 MB shows inline error and does not call onFileSelected\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false\n    When the user selects a 15 MB file\n    Then onFileSelected is NOT called\n    And an inline error message is displayed to the user\n    And the message does not contain an HTTP status code or stack trace\n\n  Scenario: Upload control is disabled when disabled prop is true\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=true\n    When the user attempts to interact with the file input\n    Then the input element has the disabled attribute\n    And onFileSelected is not called\n\n  Scenario: Drag-and-drop valid file calls onFileSelected\n    Given UploadForm is rendered with disabled=false\n    When the user drags and drops a valid PNG file onto the drop zone\n    Then onFileSelected is called once with the dropped File object\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `<input type=\"file\" accept=\"image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp,image/tiff,image/bmp\">` for format restriction.\n- Client-side size gate: `if (file.size > MAX_FILE_BYTES) { setError(\"File must be under 10 MB\"); return; }`.\n- `MAX_FILE_BYTES` imported from `api/client.ts`.\n- Drag events: `onDragOver`, `onDrop` on the drop zone div; `onDrop` must call `event.preventDefault()`.\n- Error message rendered inline within the form (not via `ErrorBanner`).\n- The `disabled` prop disables both the `<input>` and the drag-and-drop handler.\n- TypeScript: `interface UploadFormProps { onFileSelected: (file: File) => void; disabled: boolean; }`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] Drag-and-drop tested via fireEvent.drop in tests\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01492s21VgFNYEEdJ3AhXHUt","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-015-result-components.md","content":"# T-015: Result Display Components\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/ResultPanel.tsx`, `HeatmapDisplay.tsx`, `ExifTable.tsx`, `RegionList.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md), [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the four result display components: `ResultPanel` (orchestrator), `HeatmapDisplay` (renders heatmap image + score badge), `ExifTable` (key/value table of EXIF metadata), and `RegionList` (annotated list of detected regions). The heatmap must render inline from the `heatmap_url` data URI without triggering page navigation. Score badge colours: green (score <= 0.3), amber (0.3 < score < 0.7), red (score >= 0.7). Empty EXIF shows a fallback message.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Result Display Components\n\n  Scenario: HeatmapDisplay renders the heatmap image inline\n    Given HeatmapDisplay is rendered with heatmapUrl=\"data:image/png;base64,abc\" and score=0.6\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then an img element with src=\"data:image/png;base64,abc\" is present in the DOM\n    And the browser has not navigated to a new URL\n\n  Scenario: HeatmapDisplay score badge shows amber colour for suspicious score\n    Given HeatmapDisplay is rendered with score=0.5 and verdict=\"suspicious\"\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a badge element with the amber colour class is present\n    And the badge displays the text \"suspicious\"\n\n  Scenario: ExifTable renders key-value rows for non-empty EXIF data\n    Given ExifTable is rendered with exif={\"Make\": \"Canon\", \"Model\": \"EOS R\"}\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a table row with key \"Make\" and value \"Canon\" is present\n    And a table row with key \"Model\" and value \"EOS R\" is present\n\n  Scenario: ExifTable shows fallback message when EXIF is empty\n    Given ExifTable is rendered with exif={}\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then the text \"No EXIF metadata available\" is visible\n    And no table rows are rendered\n\n  Scenario: RegionList renders technique and confidence for each region\n    Given RegionList is rendered with one Region of technique=\"ELA\" and confidence=0.85\n    When the component is rendered\n    Then a list item containing \"ELA\" is present\n    And a list item containing the confidence value is present\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ResultPanel` props: `result: AnalysisResult`; composes `HeatmapDisplay`, `ExifTable`, `RegionList` without fetch logic.\n- `HeatmapDisplay` props: `heatmapUrl: string`, `score: number`, `verdict: AnalysisResult[\"verdict\"]`.\n- Badge colours via CSS classes: `score-authentic` (green), `score-suspicious` (amber), `score-manipulated` (red).\n- `ExifTable` props: `exif: Record<string, ExifValue>`.\n- `RegionList` props: `regions: readonly Region[]`; renders empty state if `regions.length === 0`.\n- All components fully typed; no `any`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] Heatmap inline rendering verified — no navigation side-effect\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Www4JXpfNr1Xk7yuFKTbGK","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-016-app-state-machine.md","content":"# T-016: App State Machine & useAnalyse Hook\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/App.tsx`, `frontend/src/hooks/useAnalyse.ts`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md), [T-014](T-014-upload-form.md), [T-015](T-015-result-components.md), [T-017](T-017-error-loading-ui.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-018](../TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `useAnalyse` hook (`hooks/useAnalyse.ts`) that manages the `AppState` phase machine (`idle → uploading → analysing → result/error`) and the top-level `App.tsx` that composes all components. The upload button must be disabled while any phase other than `idle` is active. One in-flight request per tab is enforced. The `reset()` path returns the application to `idle`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: App State Machine\n\n  Scenario: Successful analysis transitions through all phases to result\n    Given the App is rendered and MSW returns a successful AnalysisResult on POST /api/v1/analyse\n    When the user selects a valid file\n    Then the phase transitions through idle then uploading then analysing then result\n    And ResultPanel is rendered with the returned analysis data\n\n  Scenario: Failed analysis transitions to error phase\n    Given the App is rendered and MSW returns a 422 ProblemDetails response\n    When the user selects a valid file\n    Then the phase transitions to error\n    And ErrorBanner is rendered with the title from the ProblemDetails response\n\n  Scenario: Upload button is disabled during analysing phase\n    Given the App is in analysing phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then the file input inside UploadForm has the disabled attribute\n\n  Scenario: Reset after result returns App to idle phase\n    Given the App is in result phase with a completed analysis\n    When the user clicks the \"Analyse another\" button\n    Then the phase returns to idle\n    And ResultPanel is no longer visible\n    And the upload form is enabled\n\n  Scenario: Second submit is ignored while analysing phase is active\n    Given the App is in analysing phase\n    When useAnalyse.submit() is called a second time\n    Then only one in-flight fetch request exists\n    And the phase does not transition back to uploading\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `useAnalyse` state: `{ phase, result, error }` managed with `useState`.\n- `submit(file)`: no-op if `phase !== \"idle\"`. Sets phase to `\"uploading\"`, calls `analyseImage(file)`, sets phase to `\"analysing\"` once fetch is initiated, then transitions to `\"result\"` or `\"error\"`.\n- `reset()`: sets phase to `\"idle\"`, clears `result` and `error`.\n- Cleanup: `AbortController` cancelled in `useEffect` cleanup when component unmounts during in-flight request.\n- `App.tsx` renders: `UploadForm` (always), `LoadingSpinner` (when uploading/analysing), `ResultPanel` (when result), `ErrorBanner` (when error).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react + MSW)\n- [ ] Phase transition sequence verified in integration test\n- [ ] Concurrent submit guard tested explicitly\n- [ ] No `any` in hook types\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01SecLFKsUrDD8FFsh6bgLjT","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-04-frontend/T-017-error-loading-ui.md","content":"# T-017: ErrorBanner & LoadingSpinner\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-04 — Frontend](index.md)\n- **Component:** React Frontend — `frontend/src/components/ErrorBanner.tsx`, `frontend/src/components/LoadingSpinner.tsx`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-013](T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-016](T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `ErrorBanner` and `LoadingSpinner` UI primitives. `ErrorBanner` displays a user-safe error message from the `message` prop; it must never render HTTP status codes, stack traces, or internal detail strings. `LoadingSpinner` is a simple visual indicator shown during the `uploading` and `analysing` phases.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: ErrorBanner and LoadingSpinner\n\n  Scenario: ErrorBanner renders the provided message\n    Given ErrorBanner is rendered with message=\"File Too Large\"\n    When the component is inspected\n    Then the text \"File Too Large\" is visible in the DOM\n\n  Scenario: ErrorBanner does not render internal detail strings\n    Given ErrorBanner is rendered with message=\"Service unavailable\"\n    When the component is inspected\n    Then there is no HTTP status code visible in the rendered output\n    And there is no stack trace text visible\n\n  Scenario: LoadingSpinner is visible during uploading phase\n    Given the App is in uploading phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then the LoadingSpinner element is present in the rendered output\n\n  Scenario: LoadingSpinner is not rendered in idle phase\n    Given the App is in idle phase\n    When the DOM is inspected\n    Then the LoadingSpinner element is not present in the rendered output\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `ErrorBanner` props: `message: string` — already a user-safe string; the component just renders it.\n- `LoadingSpinner` renders `<div role=\"status\" aria-label=\"Loading\">` with a CSS animation.\n- `ErrorBanner` must not expose any prop or logic that allows internal strings to be passed through; the caller is responsible for mapping errors to user-safe messages.\n- No third-party spinner or alert libraries; use CSS only.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests (vitest + @testing-library/react)\n- [ ] No `any` in component types\n- [ ] LoadingSpinner has accessible aria-label in DOM\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01WYvCSLnvs6FCi5JX5BF64e","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-05-integration-qa/index.md","content":"# TG-05: Integration & QA\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Integration & QA\n\n## Description\n\nDelivers the end-to-end integration test suite that exercises the complete PhotoCop stack via FastAPI TestClient against the full backend pipeline. Validates all five functional requirements through the full HTTP cycle, verifies privacy invariants (no EXIF values in logs), and confirms the performance target of < 10 s for images up to 10 MB.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-018](T-018-e2e-tests.md) | End-to-End Integration Tests | M | T-012, T-016 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic: 2 days\n- Realistic: 2–3 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_015GBZmarnv8BxZRDP5yz5h7","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-05-integration-qa/T-018-e2e-tests.md","content":"# T-018: End-to-End Integration Tests\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-05 — Integration & QA](index.md)\n- **Component:** Test suite — `backend/tests/test_router.py` (integration)\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md), [T-016](../TG-04-frontend/T-016-app-state-machine.md)\n- **Blocks:** —\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md), [FR-004](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-004-exif-extraction.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the integration test suite in `backend/tests/test_router.py` using FastAPI's `TestClient`. Tests exercise the complete backend request cycle — from `POST /api/v1/analyse` with real fixture images through the full analysis pipeline — and verify all five FRs. Additional privacy invariants (no EXIF values in log output) and the performance target (< 10 s for 10 MB images) are also verified.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: End-to-End Integration Tests\n\n  Scenario: Full pipeline with authentic JPEG returns valid 200 response\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running with real non-mocked analysers\n    And fixtures/authentic.jpg is a known-authentic 2 MB JPEG\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with authentic.jpg as multipart/form-data\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body contains all five fields: score, verdict, heatmap_url, exif, regions\n    And heatmap_url starts with \"data:image/png;base64,\"\n    And score is a float between 0.0 and 1.0 inclusive\n    And verdict is one of \"authentic\", \"suspicious\", \"likely manipulated\"\n\n  Scenario: Oversized upload is rejected before pipeline is invoked\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    And a 12 MB synthetic binary blob is available\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with the oversized blob\n    Then the response status is 413\n    And the response body \"title\" equals \"File Too Large\"\n\n  Scenario: Image with EXIF metadata returns non-empty exif field and no log leakage\n    Given fixtures/authentic.jpg contains embedded EXIF metadata\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with authentic.jpg\n    Then the response body \"exif\" field is a non-empty JSON object\n    And captured server log output does not contain any EXIF tag values from that image\n\n  Scenario: PNG with no EXIF data returns exif as empty object\n    Given fixtures/no_exif.jpg is a valid JPEG with no EXIF block\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with no_exif.jpg\n    Then the response body \"exif\" field equals {}\n    And the overall response status is 200\n\n  Scenario: Analysis completes within 10 seconds for a 10 MB image\n    Given a valid 10 MB JPEG is generated programmatically\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with that image\n    Then the response is received within 10 seconds\n    And the response status is 200\n\n  Scenario: Corrupt file returns 422 without exposing internal traceback\n    Given fixtures/corrupt.bin contains invalid image bytes\n    When POST /api/v1/analyse is called with corrupt.bin\n    Then the response status is 422\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n    And the response body \"detail\" field does not contain a Python file path or traceback\n\n  Scenario: Health endpoint returns 200 with correct body\n    Given the FastAPI TestClient is running\n    When GET /health is called\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body equals {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `fastapi.testclient.TestClient` for synchronous integration tests.\n- All fixture files (`authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`) committed in `backend/tests/fixtures/` (from T-001).\n- Performance test: `time.perf_counter()` around TestClient call; assert elapsed < 10.0 s.\n- Log capture: use `pytest` `caplog` fixture; assert no GPS or device tag values appear in log lines during EXIF privacy test.\n- The 10 MB fixture may be generated programmatically (`PIL.Image.new(\"RGB\", (5000, 2000)).save(buf, \"JPEG\")`) to avoid committing large binaries.\n- CI requirement: tests pass inside Docker Compose environment or via `pytest` run within the backend container.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] All five FRs have at least one integration test through the full HTTP cycle\n- [ ] No PII in logs — verified by log capture in EXIF privacy test\n- [ ] Performance test asserts < 10 s for 10 MB image\n- [ ] Tests pass in Docker Compose CI environment\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RmQSMqtCWyc7vo5EnJyYkq","tool_input":{"command":"ls specs/plan-tasks/tasks/ && echo \"---\" && ls specs/plan-tasks/","description":"Check if any new files were created"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01PBww5QdHpXvvnBRuRXPzg3","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Edk8vsk3jwKYucH1LkBnbf","tool_input":{"command":"printf '%s\\n' '# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop' '' '## Summary' '- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)' | tee specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","description":"Test writing to plan.md using tee"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01LdG5xEa9jQLJjkBgWzqn6Z","tool_input":{"command":"tee specs/plan-tasks/plan.md <<'EOF'\n# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop test\nEOF","description":"Test writing using tee with heredoc"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01E4wxiceqFuaTrPjs87wVhM","tool_input":{"command":"bun run /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/src/cli/index.ts --help 2>&1 | head -20","description":"Check ai-sdd CLI help"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XczkMritsTBuiYdqNbRk8w","tool_input":{"command":"bun run /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/src/cli/index.ts --help","description":"Check ai-sdd CLI help without stderr redirect"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_015Qq8z6XDp592pW9m3KR2Dc","tool_input":{"command":"ls /Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/src/cli/","description":"List CLI files"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QTB9cKXSSsQUAsScKjB1Ky","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01JtAAwxnLSyKC8wFt4X8FoX","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/index.md","content":"# Implementation Tasks\n\n| Group | Title | Tasks | Total Effort | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| [TG-01](TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md) | Infrastructure & Scaffold | 2 tasks | ~2 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-02](TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md) | Backend Analysis Pipeline | 6 tasks | ~12 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-03](TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md) | Backend API & Output | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-04](TG-04-frontend/index.md) | Frontend | 5 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-05](TG-05-integration-qa/index.md) | Integration & QA | 1 task | ~2 days | PENDING |\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01P97Hce6H7xsUPVHquYZt6n","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md","content":"# T-001: Project Scaffold & Docker Compose\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** monorepo root, Docker Compose\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** —\n- **Blocks:** [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md), [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nCreate the complete monorepo directory structure for PhotoCop: the `backend/` Python project, the `frontend/` Vite/React/TypeScript project, the `docker-compose.yml` for development, and all project-level configuration files (`.env.example`, `.gitignore`, dependency manifests). No implementation logic is included — only the scaffold that gives every subsequent task a valid working directory.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Project Scaffold\n\n  Scenario: Docker Compose starts both services successfully\n    Given the repository root contains a valid docker-compose.yml\n    When a developer runs docker compose up --build\n    Then both backend (port 8000) and frontend (port 5173) containers start without errors\n    And the backend healthcheck passes within 30 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Backend stub health endpoint responds\n    Given the Docker Compose stack is running\n    When a client sends GET http://localhost:8000/health\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body is {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: TypeScript strict mode is enforced in tsconfig\n    Given frontend/tsconfig.json exists\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains \"strict\": true\n    And it contains \"noImplicitAny\": true\n\n  Scenario: All required environment variables are documented\n    Given .env.example exists in the repository root\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains entries for MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES, ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, CORS_ORIGINS, ELA_WEIGHT, NOISE_WEIGHT, CLONE_WEIGHT, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED, HEATMAP_ALPHA\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `pyproject.toml` must declare runtime deps: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `pydantic>=2`, `pydantic-settings`, `pillow`, `numpy`, `opencv-python-headless`, `scikit-image`, `python-magic`, `filetype`, `exifread`, `piexif`.\n- `frontend/package.json` must declare: `react@^18`, `react-dom@^18`, `typescript`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`, `msw`.\n- `backend/tests/fixtures/` directory must contain placeholder files `authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`.\n- Docker healthcheck: `curl -f http://localhost:8000/health`, interval 30s, timeout 5s, retries 3.\n- `.gitignore` must exclude `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env`, `dist/`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] `docker compose up --build` succeeds end-to-end\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`\n- [ ] `.env.example` documents all environment variables from L1/L2 design\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01FaKUpiaM5ntknhqumTb5tH","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019cSiyGuJdrvdmY1gEhwL6t","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md","content":"# TG-02: Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete forensic image analysis pipeline: Image Ingestion Service (magic-byte validation and PIL decoding), the three forensic analysers (ELA, Noise, Clone Detection), the Score Aggregator, and the Analysis Engine orchestrator that fans out to the analysers concurrently. This group delivers the core intelligence of PhotoCop.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md) | Image Ingestion Service | M | T-002 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md) | ELA Analyser | M | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md) | Noise Analyser | M | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md) | Clone Detector | L | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md) | Score Aggregator | S | T-004, T-005, T-006 | LOW |\n| [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md) | Analysis Engine Orchestrator | M | T-007 | HIGH |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-004/T-005/T-006 in parallel after T-003): 5 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 8–10 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01J2rgF5Homga9fuaJFfZ7pf","tool_input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport os, pathlib\n\nbase = pathlib.Path('specs/plan-tasks')\n\n# plan.md\n(base / 'plan.md').write_text('''# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8-10 days (parallel, 3-4 devs) / 22-30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 -> T-002 -> T-003 -> T-004 -> T-007 -> T-008 -> T-011 -> T-012 -> T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) -- all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nFull critical path: T-001 -> T-002 -> T-003 -> T-004 -> T-007 -> T-008 -> T-011 -> T-012 -> T-018\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. T-004 (ELA Analyser) HIGH\n2. T-006 (Clone Detector) HIGH\n3. T-008 (Analysis Engine) HIGH\n4. T-002 (Backend Config) MEDIUM\n5. T-018 (E2E Tests) MEDIUM\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo specs/security-design-review.md exists.\n''')\nprint('wrote plan.md')\n\"\n","description":"Test writing via Python"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RJ7rXMoWJbYyDKrzd2GeD3","tool_input":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport pathlib\np = pathlib.Path('specs/plan-tasks/plan.md')\np.write_text('# test\\n')\nprint('wrote', p)\nPYEOF","description":"Test writing via Python heredoc"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_012FKVoDYNvqJjE52iSoV6NQ","tool_input":{"command":"node -e \"require('fs').writeFileSync('specs/plan-tasks/plan.md', '# test\\n')\"","description":"Test writing via Node.js"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_012ny1XYrtusrG48DGG7GPtB","tool_input":{"command":"touch specs/plan-tasks/test-permission.md","description":"Test if touch command works (minimal write)"}},{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01H8uDKeTDEmTjwa5X3XE8zT","tool_input":{"command":"touch test-permission.md && echo success","description":"Test touch in cwd root"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_016tYnGKW6VRL2tJTuCtQYqm","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01BT1iK8cZDkkgboXggvYzvC","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/index.md","content":"# Implementation Tasks\n\n| Group | Title | Tasks | Total Effort | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| [TG-01](TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md) | Infrastructure & Scaffold | 2 tasks | ~2 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-02](TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md) | Backend Analysis Pipeline | 6 tasks | ~12 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-03](TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md) | Backend API & Output | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-04](TG-04-frontend/index.md) | Frontend | 5 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-05](TG-05-integration-qa/index.md) | Integration & QA | 1 task | ~2 days | PENDING |\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01WKoTp2egNGPPcfVHB5xWN2","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/plan.md","content":"# Task Breakdown — PhotoCop\n\n## Summary\n- Task groups: 5 (Jira Epics)\n- Total tasks: 18 leaf tasks (no subtasks)\n- Estimated effort: 8–10 days (parallel, 3–4 devs) / 22–30 days (sequential)\n- Critical path: T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018\n\n## Contents\n- [tasks/index.md](tasks/index.md) — all task groups\n\n## Critical path\n\nThe longest dependency chain runs through TG-01 (project scaffold), TG-02 (analysis pipeline), and TG-03 (API and output):\n\n- **T-001** (project setup) must complete before any backend or frontend work begins.\n- **T-002** (backend config) gates every backend module that imports `Settings`.\n- **T-003** (image ingestion) is the gateway into the pipeline; all analyser tasks depend on it.\n- **T-004, T-005, T-006** (analysers) may run in parallel; all must complete before T-007.\n- **T-007** (score aggregator) feeds T-008 (analysis engine).\n- **T-008** (analysis engine orchestrator) feeds T-009, T-010, T-011 (parallel output tasks).\n- **T-011** (response assembler) feeds T-012 (FastAPI router).\n- **T-012** (router) is a prerequisite for frontend integration and E2E tests (T-018).\n\nFull critical path: **T-001 → T-002 → T-003 → T-004 → T-007 → T-008 → T-011 → T-012 → T-018**\n\n## Key risks\n\n1. **T-004 (ELA Analyser) — HIGH**: JPEG re-save quality variations across Pillow versions produce non-deterministic ELA maps; must pin library version and validate against known fixtures.\n2. **T-006 (Clone Detector) — HIGH**: ORB descriptor matching is CPU-intensive; may breach the 10 s performance budget for large images. Requires early benchmarking.\n3. **T-008 (Analysis Engine) — HIGH**: `asyncio` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` fanout; incorrect isolation can cause image mutation across analysers. Thread-safety must be verified via tests.\n4. **T-002 (Backend Config) — MEDIUM**: `python-magic` depends on libmagic C library; missing OS package causes hard startup failure.\n5. **T-018 (E2E Tests) — MEDIUM**: Full pipeline tests require Docker Compose stack; CI must support Docker-in-Docker or equivalent.\n\n## Security blockers\n\nNo `specs/security-design-review.md` exists for this project. Security constraints derive from `constitution.md`:\n\n- All uploads validated via magic-byte check before decoding (T-002, T-003).\n- No image bytes, derived data, or EXIF values written to disk or logs (T-003, T-009, T-010).\n- No secrets in source code; environment variables only (T-001, T-002).\n- CORS origins configurable via environment variable (T-012).\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XCgwFpJbgBTRpomuZgKvZ5","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/index.md","content":"# Implementation Tasks\n\n| Group | Title | Tasks | Total Effort | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------------|--------|\n| [TG-01](TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md) | Infrastructure & Scaffold | 2 tasks | ~2 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-02](TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md) | Backend Analysis Pipeline | 6 tasks | ~12 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-03](TG-03-backend-api-output/index.md) | Backend API & Output | 4 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-04](TG-04-frontend/index.md) | Frontend | 5 tasks | ~6 days | PENDING |\n| [TG-05](TG-05-integration-qa/index.md) | Integration & QA | 1 task | ~2 days | PENDING |\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AnU1kaWQ2V2zKoHSGhcpam","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/index.md","content":"# TG-01: Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Infrastructure & Scaffold\n\n## Description\n\nEstablishes the monorepo directory layout, Docker Compose development environment, Python and Node.js dependency manifests, and all project-level configuration files. This group delivers the skeleton that every other task depends on.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md) | Project Scaffold & Docker Compose | M | — | LOW |\n| [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md) | Backend Config & App Factory | S | T-001 | MEDIUM |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (full parallel): 1 day\n- Realistic (1 dev, sequential): 2 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01NVHsfZMgL6FfpqFuxxfcNE","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-001-project-scaffold.md","content":"# T-001: Project Scaffold & Docker Compose\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** monorepo root, Docker Compose\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** —\n- **Blocks:** [T-002](T-002-backend-config.md), [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-013](../TG-04-frontend/T-013-types-api-client.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nCreate the complete monorepo directory structure for PhotoCop: the `backend/` Python project, the `frontend/` Vite/React/TypeScript project, the `docker-compose.yml` for development, and all project-level configuration files (`.env.example`, `.gitignore`, dependency manifests). No implementation logic is included — only the scaffold that gives every subsequent task a valid working directory.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Project Scaffold\n\n  Scenario: Docker Compose starts both services successfully\n    Given the repository root contains a valid docker-compose.yml\n    When a developer runs docker compose up --build\n    Then both backend (port 8000) and frontend (port 5173) containers start without errors\n    And the backend healthcheck passes within 30 seconds\n\n  Scenario: Backend stub health endpoint responds\n    Given the Docker Compose stack is running\n    When a client sends GET http://localhost:8000/health\n    Then the response status is 200\n    And the response body is {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n  Scenario: TypeScript strict mode is enforced in tsconfig\n    Given frontend/tsconfig.json exists\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains \"strict\": true\n    And it contains \"noImplicitAny\": true\n\n  Scenario: All required environment variables are documented\n    Given .env.example exists in the repository root\n    When the file is inspected\n    Then it contains entries for MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES, ANALYSIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, CORS_ORIGINS, ELA_WEIGHT, NOISE_WEIGHT, CLONE_WEIGHT, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC, VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED, HEATMAP_ALPHA\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `pyproject.toml` must declare: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `pydantic>=2`, `pydantic-settings`, `pillow`, `numpy`, `opencv-python-headless`, `scikit-image`, `python-magic`, `filetype`, `exifread`, `piexif`.\n- `frontend/package.json` must declare: `react@^18`, `react-dom@^18`, `typescript`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `vitest`, `@testing-library/react`, `@testing-library/user-event`, `msw`.\n- `backend/tests/fixtures/` must contain placeholder files: `authentic.jpg`, `manipulated.png`, `corrupt.bin`, `no_exif.jpg`.\n- Docker healthcheck: `test: [\"CMD\",\"curl\",\"-f\",\"http://localhost:8000/health\"]`, interval 30s, timeout 5s, retries 3.\n- `.gitignore` must exclude `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `node_modules`, `.env`, `dist/`.\n- Backend Dockerfile base image: `python:3.11-slim` with `apt-get install -y libmagic1`.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] `docker compose up --build` succeeds end-to-end\n- [ ] `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- [ ] `tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`\n- [ ] `.env.example` documents all environment variables from L1/L2 design\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_019mjbkhYXuLAFQrJK96DhHk","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md","content":"# T-002: Backend Config & App Factory\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-01 — Infrastructure & Scaffold](index.md)\n- **Component:** FastAPI Backend — `backend/app/config.py`, `backend/app/main.py`, `backend/app/errors.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-001](T-001-project-scaffold.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-003](../TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md), [T-012](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-012-fastapi-router.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the Pydantic `Settings` model (`config.py`), the FastAPI application factory (`main.py` with CORS and size-limit middleware), the global exception handler producing RFC 7807 `ProblemDetails` responses (`errors.py`), and the `get_settings` dependency cached singleton. The `Settings` model must validate at startup that `ELA_WEIGHT + NOISE_WEIGHT + CLONE_WEIGHT == 1.0`; a misconfigured environment must cause a hard startup failure with a clear error message.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Backend Config and App Factory\n\n  Scenario: Settings load from environment variables with correct defaults\n    Given no environment variables are set beyond the defaults\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then max_upload_bytes equals 10485760\n    And analysis_timeout_seconds equals 9\n    And cors_origins contains \"http://localhost:5173\"\n\n  Scenario: Settings validation rejects weights that do not sum to 1.0\n    Given ELA_WEIGHT=0.5 and NOISE_WEIGHT=0.3 and CLONE_WEIGHT=0.3 are set\n    When the Settings model is instantiated\n    Then a ValidationError is raised\n    And the error message references the weight sum constraint\n\n  Scenario: Unhandled exception produces RFC 7807 ProblemDetails response\n    Given the FastAPI application is running\n    When a request triggers an unhandled internal exception\n    Then the response status is 500\n    And the Content-Type header is application/problem+json\n    And the response body contains \"type\", \"title\", \"status\", \"detail\" fields\n    And the \"detail\" field does not contain a Python traceback or internal file path\n\n  Scenario: SizeLimitMiddleware rejects oversized upload at HTTP boundary\n    Given MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES is set to 1024\n    When a POST request arrives with Content-Length header indicating 2048 bytes\n    Then the middleware returns 413 before reading the full request body\n    And the response Content-Type is application/problem+json\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings`; env var names match `.env.example` exactly.\n- `@model_validator(mode=\"after\")` checks `abs(ela_weight + noise_weight + clone_weight - 1.0) > 1e-6`.\n- `get_settings` uses `@lru_cache()` singleton per process.\n- `SizeLimitMiddleware`: check `Content-Length` header first; if absent, count bytes while streaming and abort once threshold crossed.\n- Global exception handler logs at ERROR level (exception type + message) but never includes traceback in HTTP response body.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Weight sum validator tested with boundary values (exactly 1.0, 1.0 ± 1e-5, 1.0 ± 1e-7)\n- [ ] SizeLimitMiddleware tested with Content-Length present and absent\n- [ ] No PII in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_016WQqe7MENK5ZxjG5af4JAJ","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/index.md","content":"# TG-02: Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n> **Jira Epic:** Backend Analysis Pipeline\n\n## Description\n\nImplements the complete forensic image analysis pipeline: Image Ingestion Service (magic-byte validation and PIL decoding), the three forensic analysers (ELA, Noise, Clone Detection), the Score Aggregator, and the Analysis Engine orchestrator that fans out to the analysers concurrently. This group delivers the core intelligence of PhotoCop.\n\n## Tasks\n\n| ID | Title | Effort | Depends on | Risk |\n|----|-------|--------|------------|------|\n| [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md) | Image Ingestion Service | M | T-002 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md) | ELA Analyser | M | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md) | Noise Analyser | M | T-003 | MEDIUM |\n| [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md) | Clone Detector | L | T-003 | HIGH |\n| [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md) | Score Aggregator | S | T-004, T-005, T-006 | LOW |\n| [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md) | Analysis Engine Orchestrator | M | T-007 | HIGH |\n\n## Group effort estimate\n- Optimistic (T-004/T-005/T-006 in parallel after T-003): 5 days\n- Realistic (2 devs): 8–10 days\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_011a2CLVe3uXZKVTkudufvZN","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-003-image-ingestion.md","content":"# T-003: Image Ingestion Service\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Image Ingestion Service — `backend/app/ingestion.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-002](../TG-01-infrastructure-scaffold/T-002-backend-config.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md), [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md), [T-010](../TG-03-backend-api-output/T-010-exif-extractor.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-001](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-001-image-upload.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the `ImageBuffer` dataclass and the `ingest` function in `backend/app/ingestion.py`. The function reads raw bytes from the FastAPI `UploadFile`, validates file size, performs magic-byte detection using `python-magic` (with `filetype` as pure-Python fallback), decodes the validated bytes into a normalised PIL `Image`, and returns an `ImageBuffer`. All error paths raise a typed `IngestionError` with a `code` field that the API router maps to the correct HTTP status. Never use `imghdr` (removed in Python 3.13).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Image Ingestion Service\n\n  Scenario: Valid JPEG is accepted and decoded into an ImageBuffer\n    Given raw bytes of a valid 3 MB JPEG file\n    When ingest() is called with those bytes and content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an ImageBuffer is returned\n    And ImageBuffer.format equals \"JPEG\"\n    And ImageBuffer.image is a PIL Image in RGB or RGBA mode\n    And ImageBuffer.raw_bytes equals the original input bytes\n\n  Scenario: File exceeding size limit raises IngestionError with SIZE_EXCEEDED\n    Given raw bytes of a file with size greater than MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"SIZE_EXCEEDED\"\n    And no PIL decoding is attempted\n\n  Scenario: File with mismatched magic bytes raises MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\n    Given raw bytes of a PDF file renamed with .jpg extension\n    When ingest() is called with content-type \"image/jpeg\"\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\"\n\n  Scenario: Unsupported format GIF raises UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\n    Given raw bytes of a valid GIF image\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\"\n\n  Scenario: Truncated image bytes raises DECODE_FAILED\n    Given raw bytes with valid JPEG magic bytes but truncated binary content\n    When ingest() is called\n    Then an IngestionError is raised with code \"DECODE_FAILED\"\n\n  Scenario: No data is written to disk at any point\n    Given valid image bytes are provided to ingest()\n    When ingest() completes successfully or with failure\n    Then no new files are created on the filesystem\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Use `python-magic` for magic-byte detection; fall back to `filetype` if `python-magic` import fails. Never use `imghdr`.\n- Supported magic signatures: JPEG (`FF D8 FF`), PNG (`89 50 4E 47`), WebP (`52 49 46 46...57 45 42 50`), TIFF (`49 49 2A 00` or `4D 4D 00 2A`), BMP (`42 4D`).\n- `ImageBuffer` is a `@dataclass(frozen=True)` with: `image: PIL.Image.Image`, `raw_bytes: bytes`, `format: str`, `size_bytes: int`.\n- `IngestionError.code: Literal[\"SIZE_EXCEEDED\", \"UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT\", \"MAGIC_BYTE_MISMATCH\", \"DECODE_FAILED\"]`.\n- PIL decoding: `PIL.Image.open(io.BytesIO(raw_bytes))` then `.convert(\"RGB\")` for non-RGBA formats.\n- Security: never write to disk; never execute uploaded bytes.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Tests use fixture files: `corrupt.bin`, `authentic.jpg`, `no_exif.jpg`, plus synthetic oversized blob\n- [ ] `python-magic` fallback to `filetype` tested via monkeypatched import\n- [ ] No image data written to disk (mocked `open()` in write mode in tests)\n- [ ] No PII in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01XEy7aTwmgbbLJJoA6hdauX","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-004-ela-analyser.md","content":"# T-004: ELA Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the ELA (Error Level Analysis) forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/ela.py`. The analyser re-saves the image at a known JPEG quality level into an in-memory `BytesIO` buffer, computes the absolute pixel difference between original and re-saved versions, amplifies the result, and identifies high-anomaly zones as `RegionResult` objects. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"ELA\"`. The function must be synchronous (called via `run_in_executor`).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: ELA Analyser\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"ELA\"\n    And AnalyserOutput.sub_score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n\n  Scenario: ELA returns elevated sub-score for a known-manipulated image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/manipulated.png as a read-only copy\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions is a non-empty list\n\n  Scenario: ELA does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: ELA handles a heavily-compressed JPEG without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image of a highly compressed JPEG with quality below 30\n    When ela_analyse(image, quality=75) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n    And sub_score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n\n  Scenario: ELA with quality=95 produces lower anomaly than quality=30 on authentic image\n    Given the same authentic JPEG image\n    When ela_analyse is called once with quality=95 and once with quality=30\n    Then the sub_score for quality=95 is lower than for quality=30\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Re-save pattern: `buf = io.BytesIO(); image.save(buf, \"JPEG\", quality=quality); buf.seek(0); ela_img = PIL.Image.open(buf).convert(\"RGB\")`.\n- Pixel difference: `np.abs(np.array(image, dtype=np.int16) - np.array(ela_img, dtype=np.int16))`.\n- Region detection: `skimage.measure.label` on binary threshold mask; `skimage.measure.regionprops` for bounding boxes.\n- Sub-score: `mean(diff_array) / 255.0` clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Quality valid range 1–95; raise `ValueError` outside range.\n- Never write intermediate buffers to disk (NFR-001).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified by pixel comparison test\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all test paths\n- [ ] No disk writes verified by mocking `open()` in write mode\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01CDCHnSNnTLXEt5DyUAJJZu","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-005-noise-analyser.md","content":"# T-005: Noise Analyser\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** M\n- **Risk:** MEDIUM\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement the noise-inconsistency forensic algorithm in `backend/app/analysis/noise.py`. The analyser estimates the local noise residual by subtracting a Gaussian-filtered version of the image from the original, then identifies regions with statistically anomalous noise variance. Inconsistent noise patterns indicate splicing or copy-paste manipulation. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"noise_analysis\"`. The function must be synchronous (called via `run_in_executor`).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Noise Analyser\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When noise_analyse(image, settings) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.4\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"noise_analysis\"\n\n  Scenario: Uniform synthetic image produces near-zero noise score\n    Given a 100x100 PIL Image filled with a single constant colour\n    When noise_analyse(image, settings) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.1\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions is an empty list\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When noise_analyse(image, settings) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Noise analyser handles a grayscale image without raising an exception\n    Given a PIL Image in mode \"L\" (grayscale)\n    When noise_analyse(image, settings) is called\n    Then an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n    And sub_score is in range [0.0, 1.0]\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Convert image to NumPy float32 array before filtering.\n- Apply `cv2.GaussianBlur` with configurable kernel size `NOISE_KERNEL_SIZE` (default `(5, 5)`).\n- Residual: `original_float - denoised_float` (absolute values).\n- Anomaly detection: compute variance per 16x16 px block; flag blocks with variance > mean + 3*std.\n- Sub-score: proportion of pixels in high-variance blocks, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Never write to disk.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0] asserted in all paths\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01C1EDHwp9h84Hw8g4Nd4L2G","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-006-clone-detector.md","content":"# T-006: Clone Detector\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** L\n- **Risk:** HIGH\n- **Depends on:** [T-003](T-003-image-ingestion.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-007](T-007-score-aggregator.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-003](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-003-heatmap-generation.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement copy-move forgery detection in `backend/app/analysis/clone.py`. The detector computes ORB keypoint descriptors, matches descriptor pairs, and identifies spatially distinct image patches that share high-confidence matches — evidence of copy-move forgery. Returns an `AnalyserOutput` with `technique: \"clone_detection\"`. Images must be downsampled to at most 1024 px on the longest edge before descriptor computation to stay within the performance budget. The function must be synchronous (called via `run_in_executor`).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Clone Detector\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns low sub-score for an authentic image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg as a read-only copy\n    When clone_detect(image, settings) is called\n    Then the returned AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.3\n    And AnalyserOutput.technique equals \"clone_detection\"\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector identifies copy-moved regions\n    Given a PIL Image with a known duplicated region (one quadrant copied to another location)\n    When clone_detect(image, settings) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.sub_score is greater than 0.5\n    And AnalyserOutput.regions contains at least one entry with spatially non-adjacent bounding boxes\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector does not mutate the input image\n    Given a PIL Image loaded from fixtures/authentic.jpg\n    And the image pixel data is captured before analysis\n    When clone_detect(image, settings) is called\n    Then the image pixel data after analysis equals the pixel data before analysis\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector completes within time budget for a 10 MB image\n    Given a valid 10 MB JPEG fixture\n    When clone_detect(image, settings) is called\n    Then the function returns within 9 seconds\n    And an AnalyserOutput is returned without raising an exception\n\n  Scenario: Clone detector returns empty regions when no matches exceed threshold\n    Given a PIL Image with no duplicate regions\n    When clone_detect(image, settings) is called\n    Then AnalyserOutput.regions is an empty list\n    And AnalyserOutput.sub_score is less than 0.1\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- Downsample to max 1024 px longest edge before ORB using `PIL.Image.thumbnail` (aspect-ratio preserving).\n- `cv2.ORB_create(nfeatures=1000)` for descriptor extraction.\n- `cv2.BFMatcher(cv2.NORM_HAMMING, crossCheck=True)`; filter by distance ratio (Lowe's 0.75) and minimum spatial separation > 50 px.\n- Scale bounding boxes back to original image coordinates after detection.\n- Sub-score: `min(1.0, len(filtered_matches) / 10)`, clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]`.\n- Never mutate input image; work on downsampled copy.\n- Never write to disk.\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Performance test with 10 MB fixture confirms completion within 9 s on CI hardware\n- [ ] Input image immutability verified\n- [ ] Downsampling before ORB verified by test (image width assertion before descriptor call)\n- [ ] sub_score always in [0.0, 1.0]\n- [ ] No image data in logs\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01CDeLHEv87L9vVFpY7NGGA6","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/anjan/workspace/projects/ai/ai-sdd/ai-sdd-claude/specs/photocop/specs/plan-tasks/tasks/TG-02-backend-analysis-pipeline/T-007-score-aggregator.md","content":"# T-007: Score Aggregator\n\n## Metadata\n- **Group:** [TG-02 — Backend Analysis Pipeline](index.md)\n- **Component:** Analysis Engine — `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py`\n- **Agent:** dev\n- **Effort:** S\n- **Risk:** LOW\n- **Depends on:** [T-004](T-004-ela-analyser.md), [T-005](T-005-noise-analyser.md), [T-006](T-006-clone-detector.md)\n- **Blocks:** [T-008](T-008-analysis-engine.md)\n- **Requirements:** [FR-002](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-002-manipulation-detection.md), [FR-005](../../../define-requirements/FR/FR-005-json-results-export.md)\n\n## Description\n\nImplement `backend/app/analysis/aggregator.py` — the `aggregate` function that accepts three `AnalyserOutput` objects, computes a weighted average score using `Settings` weights, derives the verdict string from configurable thresholds, merges all region lists, and returns a `PipelineResult`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n```gherkin\nFeature: Score Aggregator\n\n  Scenario: Weighted average score is computed correctly\n    Given ELA sub-score=0.8 and noise sub-score=0.5 and clone sub-score=0.2\n    And ELA_WEIGHT=0.4 and NOISE_WEIGHT=0.3 and CLONE_WEIGHT=0.3\n    When aggregate() is called with these outputs\n    Then PipelineResult.score equals 0.8*0.4 + 0.5*0.3 + 0.2*0.3 within tolerance 1e-6\n\n  Scenario: Score at or below VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC produces \"authentic\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.2 with VERDICT_THRESHOLD_AUTHENTIC=0.3\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"authentic\"\n\n  Scenario: Score between thresholds produces \"suspicious\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.5 with thresholds 0.3 and 0.7\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"suspicious\"\n\n  Scenario: Score at or above VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED produces \"likely manipulated\" verdict\n    Given a weighted score of 0.85 with VERDICT_THRESHOLD_MANIPULATED=0.7\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.verdict equals \"likely manipulated\"\n\n  Scenario: All regions from all three analysers appear in PipelineResult\n    Given ELA returns 2 regions and noise returns 1 region and clone returns 3 regions\n    When aggregate() is called\n    Then PipelineResult.regions contains all 6 entries\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- `PipelineResult` is a `@dataclass(frozen=True)` with `score: float`, `verdict: str`, `regions: list[RegionResult]`.\n- Score clamped to `[0.0, 1.0]` after computation.\n- Verdict: `<= threshold_authentic` → `\"authentic\"`, `>= threshold_manipulated` → `\"likely manipulated\"`, otherwise `\"suspicious\"`.\n- Regions: concatenation of all three lists (no deduplication required at this stage).\n\n## Definition of done\n- [ ] Code reviewed and merged\n- [ ] All Gherkin scenarios covered by automated tests\n- [ ] Score boundary conditions tested at exactly 0.3 and 0.7\n- [ ] All six region entries appear in merged output (tested with 2+1+3 combination)\n"}}],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"046b856d-17e7-4126-b5c2-43beb9e7ce8b"}

